726 class ExceptionFactory
727 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
728 {
729 public:
731  static void raiseException(
733  const char* pFunctionName,
735  int lineNumber,
737  int errorCode,
739  HOBJ objectHandle = INVALID_ID,
741  const std::string& additionalInfo = "" );

744 #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
745 # define MVIMPACT_H_ // force doxygen to include mvIMPACT related functions
746 #endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
747 
748 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
750 
753 class ComponentAccess
754 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
755 {
756  friend class ComponentLocatorBase;
757 protected:
759  enum { BUFFER_INCREMENT_FACTOR = 6 };
761  HOBJ m_hObj;
763 
767  std::string compGetStringParam(
768  TOBJ_StringQuery query,
770  int param1 = 0,
772  int param2 = 0 ) const
773  {
774  char* pStr = 0;
775  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
776  std::string resultString;
777  result = OBJ_GetSWithInplaceConstruction( m_hObj, query, &pStr, stringAllocator, param1, param2 );
778  if( pStr )
779  {
780  resultString = std::string( pStr );
781  }
782  delete [] pStr;
783  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
784  {
785  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
786  }
787  return resultString;
788  }
790  explicit ComponentAccess(
791  HOBJ hObj ) : m_hObj( hObj )
792  {
793  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
794  if( ( result = OBJ_CheckHandle( m_hObj, hcmOwnerList ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
795  {
796  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
797  }
798  }
800  explicit ComponentAccess( void ) : m_hObj( INVALID_ID ) {}
802  static char* stringAllocator( const char* pBuf, size_t reqBufSize )
803  {
804  char* pStr = new char[reqBufSize];
805 #if defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER >= 1400) // is at least VC 2005 compiler?
806  errno_t result = strcpy_s( pStr, reqBufSize, pBuf );
807  result = result; // remove release build warning
808  assert( result == 0 );
809  return pStr;
810 #else
811  return strcpy( pStr, pBuf );
812 #endif // #if defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER >= 1400)
813  }
814 public:
815  virtual ~ComponentAccess( void ) {}
816 #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
817  operator HOBJ() const
819  {
820  return m_hObj;
821  }
822 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, be explicit: use method hObj(); Python variables lack a type specifier, so a conversion operator is useless for variable assignment anyhow)
823 
869  unsigned int changedCounter( void ) const
870  {
871  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
872  unsigned int changedCounter;
873  if( ( result = OBJ_GetChangedCounter( m_hObj, &changedCounter ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
874  {
875  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
876  }
877  return changedCounter;
878  }
880

896  {

900  {
901  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
902  }
903  return changedCounter;
904  }

934 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
936 
1034 class Component : public ComponentAccess
1035 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1036 {
1037 private:
1038  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1039  template<typename _FnQuery> size_t queryFeatureCount( _FnQuery pFnQuery ) const
1040  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1041  {
1042  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1043  size_t featureCount = 0;
1044  if( ( result = pFnQuery( m_hObj, 0, 0, &featureCount ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1045  {
1046  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
1047  }
1048  return featureCount;
1049  }
1050  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1051  template<typename _FnQuery> size_t queryFeatures( std::vector<Component>& v, _FnQuery pFnQuery ) const
1052  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1053  {
1054  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1055  v.clear();
1056  size_t featureCount = queryFeatureCount( pFnQuery );
1057  if( featureCount > 0 )
1058  {
1059  std::vector<HOBJ> buf;
1060  buf.resize( featureCount );
1061  if( ( result = pFnQuery( m_hObj, 0, &( *( buf.begin() ) ), &featureCount ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1062  {
1063  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
1064  }
1065  v.resize( featureCount );
1066  for( size_t i = 0; i < featureCount; i++ )
1067  {
1068  v[i] = Component( buf[i] );
1069  }
1070  }
1071  return static_cast<size_t>( v.size() );
1072  }
1073  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1074  template<typename _FnQuery> HOBJ queryFeature( _FnQuery pFnQuery, int index ) const
1075  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1076  {
1077  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1078  HOBJ hObj;
1079  size_t featureCount = 1;
1080  if( ( result = pFnQuery( m_hObj, index, &hObj, &featureCount ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1081  {
1082  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
1083  }
1084  return hObj;
1085  }
1086  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1087  template<typename _FnQuery> std::string queryAsString( _FnQuery pFnQuery ) const
1088  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1089  {
1090  size_t bufSize = DEFAULT_STRING_SIZE_LIMIT;
1091  char* pBuf = new char[bufSize];
1092  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR;
1093  while( ( result = pFnQuery( m_hObj, pBuf, bufSize ) ) == PROPHANDLING_INPUT_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL )
1094  {
1095  delete [] pBuf;
1096  bufSize *= BUFFER_INCREMENT_FACTOR;
1097  pBuf = new char[bufSize];
1098  }
1099  std::string value( pBuf );
1100  delete [] pBuf;
1101  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1102  {
1103  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
1104  }
1105  return value;
1106  }
1107 public:
1109  explicit Component(
1111  HOBJ hObj ) : ComponentAccess( hObj ) {}
1113  explicit Component( void ) {}
1114 #if !defined(WRAP_PYTHON)
1115 
1119  Component& operator++( void ) // prefix
1120  {
1121  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1122  HOBJ nextSibling;
1123  if( ( result = OBJ_GetNextSibling( m_hObj, &nextSibling ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1124  {
1125  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
1126  }
1127  m_hObj = nextSibling;
1128  return *this;
1129  }
1131 
1134  Component operator++( int ) // postfix
1135  {
1136  Component temp( *this );
1137  ++*this;
1138  return temp;
1139  }
1140 #endif // #if !defined(WRAP_PYTHON)
1141 
1145  Component firstSibling( void ) const
1146  {
1147  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1148  HOBJ hNew = INVALID_ID;

1152  }

1173

1177  {

1668 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1670 
1677 class ComponentCallback
1678 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1679 {
1680 #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
1681  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1682  struct CallbackUserData
1683  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1684  {
1685  void* pUserData_;
1686  ComponentCallback* pCallback_;
1687  explicit CallbackUserData() : pUserData_( 0 ), pCallback_( 0 ) {}
1688  };
1689  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1690  struct ReferenceCountedData
1691  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1692  {
1693  CallbackHandle handle_;
1694  CallbackUserData callbackUserData_;
1695  std::set<HOBJ> objectsRegistered_;
1696  int m_refCnt;
1697  ReferenceCountedData() : handle_( 0 ), callbackUserData_(), objectsRegistered_(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
1698  }* m_pRefData;
1699 #endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
1700 
1701  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1702  static void DMR_CALL myCallback( HOBJ hObj, void* pUserData )
1703  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1704  {
1705  Component c( hObj );
1706  CallbackUserData* p = reinterpret_cast<CallbackUserData*>( pUserData );
1707  p->pCallback_->execute( c, p->pUserData_ );
1708  }
1709  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1710  void dealloc( void )
1711  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1712  {
1713  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
1714  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
1715  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
1716  {
1717  OBJ_DeleteCallback( m_pRefData->handle_ );
1718  delete m_pRefData;
1719  m_pRefData = 0;
1720  }
1721  }
1722 public:
1724  explicit ComponentCallback(
1728  void* pUserData = 0 ) : m_pRefData( new ReferenceCountedData() )
1729  {
1730  m_pRefData->callbackUserData_.pUserData_ = pUserData;
1731  m_pRefData->callbackUserData_.pCallback_ = this;
1732  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_CreateCallback( ctOnChanged, myCallback, &m_pRefData->callbackUserData_, &m_pRefData->handle_ );
1733  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1734  {
1735  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID );
1736  }
1737  }
1739 
1745  explicit ComponentCallback( const ComponentCallback& src ) : m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData )
1746  {
1747  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
1748  }
1750 
1754  virtual ~ComponentCallback()
1755  {
1756  dealloc();
1757  }
1758 #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
1759  ComponentCallback& operator=( const ComponentCallback& rhs )
1761  {
1762  if( this != &rhs )
1763  {
1764  dealloc();
1765  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
1766  // inc. the NEW reference count
1767  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
1768  }
1769  return *this;
1770  }
1771 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
1772 
1778  bool isComponentRegistered(
1780  Component c ) const
1781  {
1782  return m_pRefData->objectsRegistered_.find( c.hObj() ) != m_pRefData->objectsRegistered_.end();
1783  }
1785 
1790  bool registerComponent(
1792  Component c )
1793  {
1794  if( isComponentRegistered( c ) )
1795  {
1796  return false;
1797  }
1798  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_AttachCallback( c.hObj(), m_pRefData->handle_ );
1799  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1800  {
1801  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID );
1802  }
1803  m_pRefData->objectsRegistered_.insert( c.hObj() );
1804  return true;
1805  }
1807 
1812  bool unregisterComponent(
1814  Component c )
1815  {
1816  std::set<HOBJ>::iterator it = m_pRefData->objectsRegistered_.find( c.hObj() );
1817  if( it == m_pRefData->objectsRegistered_.end() )
1818  {
1819  return false;
1820  }
1821  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_DetachCallback( c.hObj(), m_pRefData->handle_ );
1822  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1823  {
1824  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID );
1825  }
1826  m_pRefData->objectsRegistered_.erase( *it );
1827  return true;
1828  }
1830 
1839  virtual void execute(
1841  Component& /*c*/,
1844  void* /*pUserData*/ ) {}
1845 };
1846 
1847 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1849 
1859 class ComponentLocatorBase : public ComponentAccess
1860 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1861 {
1862  HLIST m_searchbase;
1863 public:
1865  explicit ComponentLocatorBase() : m_searchbase( INVALID_ID ) {}
1867  explicit ComponentLocatorBase(
1870  HLIST baselist ) : ComponentAccess( baselist ), m_searchbase( baselist ) {}
1872  explicit ComponentLocatorBase(
1875  HLIST baselist,
1877  const std::string& pathToSearchBase ) : ComponentAccess( baselist ), m_searchbase( INVALID_ID )
1878  {
1879  bindSearchBase( baselist, pathToSearchBase );
1880  }
1882 
1888  bool bindComponent(
1889  Component& access,
1891  const std::string& name,
1897  int searchMode = 0,
1902  int maxSearchDepth = INT_MAX ) const
1903  {
1904  access.m_hObj = findComponent( name, searchMode, maxSearchDepth );
1905  return access.isValid();
1906  }
1908 
1912  HLIST bindSearchBase(
1914  HLIST baselist,
1916  const std::string& pathToSearchBase = "" )
1917  {
1918  if( pathToSearchBase.empty() )
1919  {
1920  m_hObj = m_searchbase = baselist;
1921  }
1922  else
1923  {
1924  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1925  HLIST hList;
1926  if( ( result = OBJ_GetHandleEx( baselist, pathToSearchBase.c_str(), &hList, smIgnoreProperties | smIgnoreMethods, 0 ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1927  {
1928  std::string explanation = "feature list '" + pathToSearchBase + "' is not available for this device ";
1929  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, baselist, explanation );
1930  }
1931  m_hObj = baselist;
1932  m_searchbase = hList;
1933  }
1934  return m_searchbase;
1935  }
1937 
1941  HOBJ findComponent(
1943  const std::string& name,
1949  int searchMode = 0,
1954  int maxSearchDepth = INT_MAX ) const
1955  {
1956  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
1957  HOBJ hObj;
1958  if( ( result = OBJ_GetHandleEx( m_searchbase, name.c_str(), &hObj, searchMode, maxSearchDepth ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
1959  {
1960  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_searchbase );
1961  }
1962  return hObj;
1963  }
1965 
1968  HLIST searchbase_id( void ) const
1969  {
1970  return m_searchbase;
1971  }
1972 };
1973

1993  explicit ComponentLocator(

1998  explicit ComponentLocator(

2002  const std::string& pathToSearchBase ) : ComponentLocatorBase( baselist, pathToSearchBase ) {}

2157 class Method : public Component
2158 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2159 {
2160  // do not allow assignments
2161  Method& operator=( const Method& );
2162 public:
2164  explicit Method(
2166  HOBJ hMeth ) : Component( hMeth )
2167  {
2168  if( !isMeth() )
2169  {
2170  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, PROPHANDLING_NOT_A_METHOD, hMeth );
2171  }
2172  }
2174  explicit Method() {}
2176 
2211  int call(
2213  const std::string& params,
2215  const std::string& delimiters = " " ) const
2216  {
2217  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
2218  int retval;
2219  if( ( result = OBJ_Execute( m_hObj, params.c_str(), delimiters.c_str(), &retval ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
2220  {
2221  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
2222  }
2223  return retval;
2224  }
2226 
2237  int call( void ) const
2238  {
2239  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
2240  int retval;
2241  if( ( result = OBJ_Execute( m_hObj, 0, 0, &retval ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
2242  {
2243  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
2244  }
2245  return retval;
2246  }
2248 
2271  std::string paramList( void ) const
2272  {

2274  }
2275 };

2376 class Property : public Component
2377 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2378 {
2379  // do not allow assignments! This makes sure the user can't assign e.g. the
2380  // gain property to the property for controlling the expose time
2381  Property& operator=( const Property& );
2382  bool isConstDefinedInternal( TPropertyLimits constant ) const
2383  {
2384  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
2385  unsigned int isDefined;
2386  if( ( result = OBJ_IsConstantDefined( m_hObj, constant, &isDefined ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
2387  {
2388  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
2389  }
2390  return isDefined != 0;
2391  }
2392 protected:
2393  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2394  int valuesToRead( int start, int end ) const
2395  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2396  {
2397  if( start < 0 )
2398  {
2399  // when reading a set of values, these can't include limits or any other value associated with
2400  // a negative index parameter to avoid confusion cause by END_OF_LIST
2401  // having the same value as PROP_MAX_VAL.
2402  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, PROPHANDLING_INVALID_INPUT_PARAMETER, m_hObj );
2403  }
2404  return ( end == END_OF_LIST ) ? ( valCount() - start ) : ( end - start + 1 );
2405  }
2406 public:
2408 
2412  explicit Property( void ) {}
2414 
2419  explicit Property(
2421  HOBJ hProp ) : Component( hProp )
2422  {
2423  if( !isProp() )
2424  {
2425  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, PROPHANDLING_NOT_A_PROPERTY, hProp );
2426  }
2427  }

2825  HOBJ hProp ) : Property( hProp )
2826  {
2827  if( type() != ctPropFloat )
2828  {
2829  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, PROPHANDLING_INVALID_PROP_VALUE_TYPE, hProp );
2830  }
2831  }
2832 #if !defined(DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS) && !defined(WRAP_ANY)

2848  const EnumPropertyF& getTranslationDict(
2850  std::vector<std::pair<std::string, ZYX> >& sequence ) const
2851  {
2852  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR;
2853  unsigned int size = dictSize();
2854 
2855  double* pVal = new double[size];
2856  char** ppBuf = new char* [size];
2857  size_t bufSize = DEFAULT_STRING_SIZE_LIMIT;
2858 
2859  for( size_t i = 0; i < size; i++ )
2860  {
2861  ppBuf[i] = new char[bufSize];
2862  }
2863 
2864  while( ( result = OBJ_GetFDictEntries( m_hObj, ppBuf, bufSize, pVal, size ) ) == PROPHANDLING_INPUT_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL )
2865  {
2866  bufSize *= BUFFER_INCREMENT_FACTOR;
2867  for( size_t i = 0; i < size; i++ )
2868  {
2869  delete [] ppBuf[i];
2870  ppBuf[i] = new char[bufSize];
2871  }
2872  }
2873 
2874  if( result == PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
2875  {
2876  sequence.resize( size );
2877  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < size; i++ )
2878  {
2879  sequence[i] = std::pair<std::string, ZYX>( ppBuf[i], static_cast<ZYX>( pVal[i] ) );
2880  }
2881  }
2882 
2883  for( size_t i = 0; i < size; i++ )
2884  {
2885  delete [] ppBuf[i];
2886  }
2887  delete [] ppBuf;
2888  delete [] pVal;
2889 
2890  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
2891  {
2892  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
2893  }
2894  return *this;
2895  }
2897

2910  while( ( result = OBJ_GetFDictEntry( m_hObj, pTranslationString, bufSize, 0, index ) ) == PROPHANDLING_INPUT_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL )
2911  {
2912  bufSize *= BUFFER_INCREMENT_FACTOR;
2913  delete [] pTranslationString;

3125  void read(
3127  std::vector<ZYX>& sequence,
3129  int start = 0,
3131  int end = END_OF_LIST ) const
3132  {
3133  unsigned int valCnt = valuesToRead( start, end );
3134  sequence.resize( valCnt );
3135  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < valCnt; i++ )
3136  {
3137  sequence[i] = read( i + start );
3138  }
3139  }
3141 
3146  void read(
3148  std::vector<ZYX>& sequence,
3151  bool boAtomic,
3153  int start = 0,
3155  int end = END_OF_LIST ) const
3156  {
3157  if( boAtomic )
3158  {
3159  unsigned int valCnt = valuesToRead( start, end );
3160  sequence.resize( valCnt );
3161  double* pValues = new double[valCnt];
3162  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_GetFArray( m_hObj, pValues, valCnt, start );
3163  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < valCnt; i++ )
3164  {
3165  sequence[i] = static_cast<ZYX>( pValues[i] );
3166  }
3167  delete [] pValues;
3168  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
3169  {
3170  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
3171  }
3172  }
3173  else
3174  {
3175  read( sequence, start, end );
3176  }
3177  }
3179 
3184  const EnumPropertyF& write(
3186  ZYX value,
3188  int index = 0 ) const
3189  {
3190  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
3191  if( ( result = OBJ_SetF( m_hObj, static_cast<double>( value ), index ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
3192  {
3193  std::ostringstream oss;
3194  oss << value;
3195  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj, oss.str() );
3196  }
3197  return *this;
3198  }

3212  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )

3224  const EnumPropertyF& write(
3226  const std::vector<ZYX>& sequence,

3231  int index = 0 ) const
3232  {
3233  if( boAtomic )
3234  {
3235  const unsigned int valCnt = static_cast<unsigned int>( sequence.size() );

3238  {
3239  pValues[i] = sequence[i];
3240  }
3241  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_SetFArray( m_hObj, pValues, valCnt, index );
3242  delete [] pValues;

3244  {
3245  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
3246  }
3247  return *this;
3248  }
3249  else
3250  {
3251  return write( sequence, index );
3252  }
3253  }

3432  {

3434  for( size_t i = 0; i < size; i++ )
3435  {
3436  delete [] ppBuf[i];
3437  ppBuf[i] = new char[bufSize];
3438  }
3439  }
3440 
3441  if( result == PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
3442  {
3443  sequence.resize( size );
3444  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < size; i++ )
3445  {
3446  sequence[i] = std::string( ppBuf[i] );
3447  }
3448  }
3449 
3450  for( size_t i = 0; i < size; i++ )
3451  {
3452  delete [] ppBuf[i];
3453  }
3454  delete [] ppBuf;
3455 
3456  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
3457  {
3458  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
3459  }
3460  return *this;
3461  }

4238  unsigned int valCnt = valuesToRead( start, end );
4239  sequence.resize( valCnt );
4240  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < valCnt; i++ )
4241  {
4242  sequence[i] = read( i + start );
4243  }
4244  }
4246 
4251  void read(
4253  std::vector<ZYX>& sequence,
4256  bool boAtomic,
4258  int start = 0,
4260  int end = END_OF_LIST ) const
4261  {
4262  if( boAtomic )
4263  {
4264  unsigned int valCnt = valuesToRead( start, end );
4265  sequence.resize( valCnt );
4266  int64_type* pValues = new int64_type[valCnt];
4267  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_GetI64Array( m_hObj, pValues, valCnt, start );
4268  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < valCnt; i++ )
4269  {
4270  sequence[i] = static_cast<ZYX>( pValues[i] );
4271  }
4272  delete [] pValues;
4273  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
4274  {
4275  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
4276  }
4277  }
4278  else
4279  {
4280  read( sequence, start, end );
4281  }
4282  }
4284 
4289  const EnumPropertyI64& write(
4291  ZYX value,
4293  int index = 0 ) const
4294  {
4295  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result;
4296  if( ( result = OBJ_SetI64( m_hObj, static_cast<int64_type>( value ), index ) ) != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
4297  {
4298  std::ostringstream oss;
4299 #if defined(_MSC_VER) && ( _MSC_VER < 1300 ) // is 'old' Microsoft VC 6 compiler?
4300  oss << static_cast<int>( value ); // this compiler has trouble with 64 bit integer data types as it is quite old... truncate the parameter as it's just part of a exception message anyway
4301 #else
4302  oss << value;
4303 #endif // #if defined(_MSC_VER) && ( _MSC_VER < 1300 ) // is 'old' Microsoft VC 6 compiler?
4304  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj, oss.str() );
4305  }
4306  return *this;
4307  }
4309 
4314  const EnumPropertyI64& write(
4316  const std::vector<ZYX>& sequence,
4318  int index = 0 ) const
4319  {
4320  int vSize = static_cast<int>( sequence.size() );
4321  for( int i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
4322  {
4323  write( sequence[i], index + i );
4324  }
4325  return *this;
4326  }
4328 
4333  const EnumPropertyI64& write(
4335  const std::vector<ZYX>& sequence,
4338  bool boAtomic,
4340  int index = 0 ) const
4341  {
4342  if( boAtomic )
4343  {
4344  const unsigned int valCnt = static_cast<unsigned int>( sequence.size() );
4345  int64_type* pValues = new int64_type[valCnt];
4346  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < valCnt; i++ )
4347  {
4348  pValues[i] = static_cast<int64_type>( sequence[i] );
4349  }
4350  TPROPHANDLING_ERROR result = OBJ_SetI64Array( m_hObj, pValues, valCnt, index );
4351  delete [] pValues;
4352  if( result != PROPHANDLING_NO_ERROR )
4353  {
4354  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, m_hObj );
4355  }
4356  return *this;
4357  }
4358  else
4359  {
4360  return write( sequence, index );
4361  }
4362  }
4363 };

4923 class UserData
4924 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4930  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4931  explicit UserData( HDEV hDev ) : m_boAvailable( false ), m_hDev( hDev ), m_userDataEntryLocator( hDev ),
4932  reconnectBehaviour(), memoryAvailable_bytes(), memoryConsumed_bytes()
4933  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4934  {
4935  init();
4936  }
4938  UserData& operator=( const UserData& rhs )
4939  {
4940  if( this != &rhs )
4941  {
4942  m_boAvailable = false;
4943  m_hDev = rhs.m_hDev;
4944  m_userDataEntryLocator.bindSearchBase( rhs.m_hDev );
4945  init();
4946  }
4947  return *this;
4948  }
4949  void init( void )
4950  {
4951  // check if user data is supported
4952  HOBJ hUserData = m_userDataEntryLocator.findComponent( "UserData" );
4953  if( hUserData != INVALID_ID )
4954  {
4955  Component userData( hUserData );
4956  // check if the driver supports the new enhanced user data access
4957  if( userData.isList() )
4958  {
4959  m_userDataEntryLocator.bindSearchBase( m_userDataEntryLocator.searchbase_id(), "UserData" );
4960  m_userDataEntryLocator.bindComponent( reconnectBehaviour, "ReconnectBehaviour" );
4961  m_userDataEntryLocator.bindComponent( memoryAvailable_bytes, "MemoryAvailable_bytes" );
4962  m_userDataEntryLocator.bindComponent( memoryConsumed_bytes, "MemoryConsumed_bytes" );
4963  m_userDataEntryLocator.bindSearchBase( m_userDataEntryLocator.searchbase_id(), "Entries" );
4964  m_boAvailable = true;
4965  }
4966  }
4967  }
4968 public:
4970 
4981  UserDataEntry createEntry( void )
4982  {
4983  HLIST hList;
4984  TDMR_ERROR result = DMR_CreateUserDataEntry( m_hDev, &hList );
4985  if( result != DMR_NO_ERROR )
4986  {
4987  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result );
4988  }
4989  return UserDataEntry( hList );
4990  }

5046  void validUserDataEntryIndexes(
5048  std::vector<int>& sequence ) const
5049  {
5050  sequence.clear();
5051  ComponentIterator it( m_userDataEntryLocator.searchbase_id() );
5052  if( !it.isValid() )
5053  {
5054  return;
5055  }
5056  it = it.firstChild();
5057  if( !it.isValid() )
5058  {
5059  return;
5060  }
5061  std::string::size_type indexStart = it.name().find_first_of( "0123456789" );
5062  while( it.isValid() )
5063  {
5064  sequence.push_back( atoi( it.name().substr( indexStart ).c_str() ) );
5065  ++it;
5066  }
5067  }

5161 class Device

5182  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5183  {

5186  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )

5188  delete m_pRefData;
5189  m_pRefData = 0;

5276  {

5278  {

5280  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
5281  // inc. the NEW reference count

5288 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)

5792 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5794 
5943 class DeviceManager
5944 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5945 {
5946  typedef std::vector<Device*> DevVector;
5947  HDMR m_deviceBaseList;
5948  mutable DevVector m_devVector;
5949  mutable unsigned int m_lastChangedCounter;
5950  int* m_pRefCnt;
5951  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5952  void dealloc( void )
5953  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5954  {
5955  --( *m_pRefCnt );
5956  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < m_devVector.size(); i++ )
5957  {
5958  delete m_devVector[i];
5959  }
5960  // free reference count memory if no one uses it anymore
5961  if( *m_pRefCnt == 0 )
5962  {
5963  delete m_pRefCnt;
5964  m_pRefCnt = 0;
5965  }
5966  }
5967  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5968  Device* getDevice( TDMR_DeviceSearchMode mode, const std::string& search_string, unsigned int devNr, char wildcard ) const
5969  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5970  {
5971  updateInfoVector();
5972  Device* pResult = 0;
5973  HDEV device;
5974  if( DMR_GetDevice( &device, mode, search_string.c_str(), devNr, wildcard ) == DMR_NO_ERROR )
5975  {
5976  DevVector::size_type vSize = m_devVector.size();
5977  for( DevVector::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
5978  {
5979  if( m_devVector[i]->hDev() == device )
5980  {
5981  pResult = m_devVector[i];
5982  break;
5983  }
5984  }
5985  }
5986  return pResult;
5987  }
5988  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5989  bool updateInfoVector( void ) const
5990  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5991  {
5992  ComponentIterator iter( m_deviceBaseList );
5993  unsigned int changedCount = iter.changedCounter();
5994  if( m_lastChangedCounter == changedCount )
5995  {
5996  return false;
5997  }
5998 
5999  m_lastChangedCounter = changedCount;
6000 
6001  unsigned int curDevCnt = 0;
6002  size_t vSize = m_devVector.size();
6003  DMR_GetDeviceCount( &curDevCnt );
6004  if( curDevCnt <= static_cast<unsigned int>( vSize ) )
6005  {
6006  return false;
6007  }
6008 
6009  HDEV hDev = INVALID_ID;
6010  for( size_t i = vSize; i < curDevCnt; i++ )
6011  {
6012  DMR_GetDevice( &hDev, dmdsmSerial, "*", static_cast<unsigned int>( i ), '*' );
6013  if( hDev != INVALID_ID )
6014  {
6015  m_devVector.push_back( new Device( hDev ) );
6016  }
6017  }
6018  return true;
6019  }
6020 public:
6022 
6027  explicit DeviceManager( void ) : m_deviceBaseList( INVALID_ID ), m_devVector(), m_lastChangedCounter( 0 ), m_pRefCnt( 0 )
6028  {
6029  TDMR_ERROR result;
6030  if( ( result = DMR_Init( &m_deviceBaseList ) ) != DMR_NO_ERROR )
6031  {
6032  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID, "DMR_Init failed" );
6033  }
6034  m_pRefCnt = new int();
6035  *m_pRefCnt = 1;
6036  }
6038 
6043  explicit DeviceManager( const DeviceManager& src ) : m_deviceBaseList( INVALID_ID ), m_devVector(), m_lastChangedCounter( 0 ), m_pRefCnt( src.m_pRefCnt )
6044  {
6045  // we don't need to copy data as the necessary updates are done anyway.
6046  // But we have to call the underlying C-API to achieve correct reference counting.
6047  TDMR_ERROR result;
6048  if( ( result = DMR_Init( &m_deviceBaseList ) ) != DMR_NO_ERROR )
6049  {
6050  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID, "DMR_Init failed" );
6051  }
6052  ++( *m_pRefCnt );
6053  }
6054 #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
6055  DeviceManager& operator=( const DeviceManager& rhs )
6057  {
6058  if( this != &rhs )
6059  {
6060  dealloc();
6061  m_pRefCnt = rhs.m_pRefCnt;
6062  // inc. the NEW reference count
6063  ++( *m_pRefCnt );
6064  // this will fill the device vector with up to date data the next time someone asks
6065  // for a device.
6066  m_lastChangedCounter = 0;
6067  m_devVector.clear();
6068  }
6069  return *this;
6070  }
6071 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
6072 
6079  virtual ~DeviceManager( void )
6080  {
6081  dealloc();
6082  DMR_Close();
6083  }
6085 
6092  static std::string getVersionAsString(
6094  TLibraryQuery libraryQuery )
6095  {
6096  return DMR_GetVersion( libraryQuery );
6097  }
6098 #if !defined(DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS) && !defined(WRAP_ANY)
6099  HDMR getInternalHandle( void ) const
6101  {
6102  return m_deviceBaseList;
6103  }
6104 #endif // !defined(DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS) && !defined(WRAP_ANY)
6105 #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
6106 
6124  Device* operator[](
6126  unsigned int index ) const
6127  {
6128  return getDevice( index );
6129  }
6130 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, use public method getDevice)
6131 
6140  unsigned int changedCount( void ) const
6141  {
6142  return Component( m_deviceBaseList ).changedCounter();
6143  }
6145 
6153  unsigned int deviceCount( void ) const
6154  {
6155  updateInfoVector();
6156  return static_cast<unsigned int>( m_devVector.size() );
6157  }
6159 
6187  void updateDeviceList( void ) const
6188  {
6189  TDMR_ERROR result = DMR_NO_ERROR;
6190  if( ( result = DMR_UpdateDeviceList( 0, 0 ) ) != DMR_NO_ERROR )
6191  {
6192  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result );
6193  }
6194  }
6196 
6213  Device* getDevice(
6215  unsigned int index ) const
6216  {
6217  updateInfoVector();
6218  return m_devVector.at( index );
6219  }
6221 
6249  Device* getDeviceBySerial(
6251  const std::string& serial = "",
6253  unsigned int devNr = 0,
6255  char wildcard = '*' ) const
6256  {
6257  return getDevice( dmdsmSerial, serial, devNr, wildcard );
6258  }
6260 
6289  Device* getDeviceByFamily(

6293  unsigned int devNr = 0,

6568 class DeviceComponentLocator : public ComponentLocatorBase
6569 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6570 {
6571 public:
6573  explicit DeviceComponentLocator() : ComponentLocatorBase() {}
6575  explicit DeviceComponentLocator(
6578  HLIST baselist ) : ComponentLocatorBase( baselist ) {}
6580  explicit DeviceComponentLocator(
6583  HLIST baselist,
6585  const std::string& pathToSearchBase ) : ComponentLocatorBase( baselist, pathToSearchBase ) {}
6587  explicit DeviceComponentLocator(
6590  Device* pDev,
6592  TDeviceListType deviceListType,
6595  const std::string& sublistName = "" ) : ComponentLocatorBase()
6596  {
6597  bindSearchBaseList( pDev, deviceListType, sublistName );
6598  }
6600 
6604  HLIST bindSearchBaseList(
6607  Device* pDev,
6609  TDeviceListType deviceListType,
6611  const std::string& sublistName = "" )
6612  {
6613  if( !pDev->isOpen() )
6614  {
6615  pDev->open();
6616  }
6617 
6618  HLIST hList;
6619  TDMR_ERROR result;
6620  if( ( result = DMR_FindList( pDev->hDrv(), ( sublistName.length() == 0 ) ? 0 : sublistName.c_str(), static_cast<TDMR_ListType>( deviceListType ), 0, &hList ) ) != DMR_NO_ERROR )
6621  {
6622  std::ostringstream oss;
6623  oss << "Couldn't find list '" << sublistName << "'(type: " << deviceListType << ")";
6624  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID, oss.str() );
6625  }
6626  bindSearchBase( hList );
6627  return searchbase_id();
6628  }
6629 };

6642 class ImageBufferDesc
6643 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6644 {
6645 #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
6646  friend class Request;
6647  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6648  struct ReferenceCountedData
6649  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6650  {
6651  int m_refCnt;
6652  bool m_boBufferAllocated;
6653  ImageBuffer* m_pBuffer;
6654  ReferenceCountedData( bool boAllocated = false, ImageBuffer* pBuffer = 0 )
6655  : m_refCnt( 1 ), m_boBufferAllocated( boAllocated ), m_pBuffer( pBuffer ) {}
6656  ~ReferenceCountedData()
6657  {
6658  if( m_pBuffer )
6659  {
6660  if( m_boBufferAllocated )
6661  {
6662  DMR_ReleaseImageBuffer( &m_pBuffer );
6663  }
6664  else
6665  {
6666  DMR_ReleaseImageRequestBufferDesc( &m_pBuffer );
6667  }
6668  }
6669  }
6670  // make sure there are NO assignments or copy constructions by accident!
6671  ReferenceCountedData& operator=( const ReferenceCountedData& rhs );
6672  ReferenceCountedData( const ReferenceCountedData& src );
6673  }* m_pRefData;
6674  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6675  void dealloc( void )
6676  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6677  {
6678  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
6679  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
6680  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
6681  {
6682  delete m_pRefData;
6683  m_pRefData = 0;
6684  }
6685  }
6686  explicit ImageBufferDesc( bool boAllocated, ImageBuffer* pBuf ) : m_pRefData( new ImageBufferDesc::ReferenceCountedData( boAllocated, pBuf ) ) {}
6687 #endif // DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
6688 public:
6690 
6696  ImageBufferDesc(
6698  const ImageBufferDesc& source ) : m_pRefData( source.m_pRefData )
6699  {
6700  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
6701  }
6703 
6707  explicit ImageBufferDesc(
6710  int channelCount ) : m_pRefData( new ImageBufferDesc::ReferenceCountedData() )
6711  {
6712  DMR_AllocImageRequestBufferDesc( &( m_pRefData->m_pBuffer ), channelCount );
6713  }
6715 
6723  explicit ImageBufferDesc(
6726  TImageBufferPixelFormat pixelFormat,
6729  int width,
6732  int height ) : m_pRefData( new ImageBufferDesc::ReferenceCountedData( true ) )
6733  {
6734  DMR_AllocImageBuffer( &( m_pRefData->m_pBuffer ), pixelFormat, width, height );
6735  }
6737  ~ImageBufferDesc()
6738  {
6739  dealloc();
6740  }
6741 #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
6742 
6749  ImageBufferDesc& operator=( const ImageBufferDesc& rhs )
6750  {
6751  if( this != &rhs )
6752  {
6753  dealloc();
6754  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
6755  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
6756  }
6757  return *this;
6758  }
6759 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
6760 
6767  ImageBufferDesc clone( void ) const
6768  {
6769  ImageBuffer* pDst = 0;
6770  DMR_CopyImageBuffer( m_pRefData->m_pBuffer, &pDst, 0 );
6771  return ImageBufferDesc( true, pDst );
6772  }
6774 
6777  ImageBuffer* getBuffer( void ) const
6778  {
6779  return m_pRefData->m_pBuffer;
6780  }
6781 };

6783 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6785 
6804 class Request
6805 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6806 {
6807  // only the function interface object is allowed to create new requests as
6808  // it maintains an internal reference to each request created.
6809  friend class FunctionInterface;
6810 protected:
6811 #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
6812  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6813  struct ReferenceCountedData
6814  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6815  {
6816  int m_requestNr;
6817  mutable ImageBufferDesc m_imageBufferDesc;
6818  Device* m_pDev;
6819  DeviceComponentLocator m_locator;
6820  ComponentIterator m_infoIterator;
6821  ComponentIterator m_info_imageProcessingResultsIterator;
6822  std::vector<PropertyI64*> m_chunkCounterValues;
6823  std::vector<PropertyF*> m_chunkTimerValues;
6824  std::vector<PropertyF*> m_chunkGains;
6825  std::map<std::string, unsigned int> m_chunkGainString2IndexMap;
6826  unsigned int m_refCnt;
6827  ReferenceCountedData( Device* pDev, int requestNr ) : m_requestNr( requestNr ), m_imageBufferDesc( 1 ), m_pDev( pDev ),
6828  m_locator(), m_infoIterator(), m_info_imageProcessingResultsIterator(), m_chunkCounterValues(), m_chunkTimerValues(), m_chunkGains(), m_chunkGainString2IndexMap(), m_refCnt( 1 )
6829  {
6830  if( m_requestNr >= 0 )
6831  {
6832  std::ostringstream oss;
6833  oss << "Entry " << m_requestNr;
6834  m_locator = DeviceComponentLocator( m_pDev, dltRequest, oss.str() );
6835  }
6836  else
6837  {
6838  m_locator = DeviceComponentLocator( m_pDev, dltInfo, "CurrentRequestLayout" );
6839  }
6840  }
6841  ~ReferenceCountedData()
6842  {
6843  const std::vector<PropertyI64*>::size_type cntcc = m_chunkCounterValues.size();
6844  for( std::vector<PropertyI64*>::size_type i = 0; i < cntcc; i++ )
6845  {
6846  delete m_chunkCounterValues[i];
6847  }
6848  const std::vector<PropertyF*>::size_type cntct = m_chunkTimerValues.size();
6849  for( std::vector<PropertyF*>::size_type j = 0; j < cntct; j++ )
6850  {
6851  delete m_chunkTimerValues[j];
6852  }
6853  const std::vector<PropertyF*>::size_type cntcg = m_chunkGains.size();
6854  for( std::vector<PropertyF*>::size_type k = 0; k < cntcg; k++ )
6855  {
6856  delete m_chunkGains[k];
6857  }
6858  }
6859  // make sure there are NO assignments or copy constructions by accident!
6860  ReferenceCountedData( const ReferenceCountedData& src );
6861  ReferenceCountedData& operator=( const ReferenceCountedData& rhs );
6862  void collectChunkFeatures( ComponentIterator it )
6863  {
6864  while( it.isValid() )
6865  {
6866  switch( it.type() )
6867  {
6868  case ctList:
6869  collectChunkFeatures( it.firstChild() );
6870  break;
6871  case ctPropInt64:
6872  {
6873  const std::string name( it.name() );
6874  if( ( name == "ChunkCounterValue" ) || ( name == "ChunkCounter" ) ) // the latter name is the one that became deprecated with GenICam SFNC 1.5
6875  {
6876  m_chunkCounterValues.push_back( new PropertyI64( it.hObj() ) );
6877  }
6878  }
6879  break;
6880  case ctPropFloat:
6881  {
6882  const std::string name( it.name() );
6883  if( ( name == "ChunkTimerValue" ) || ( name == "ChunkTimer" ) ) // the latter name is the one that became deprecated with GenICam SFNC 1.5
6884  {
6885  m_chunkTimerValues.push_back( new PropertyF( it.hObj() ) );
6886  }
6887  else if( name == "ChunkGain" )
6888  {
6889  m_chunkGains.push_back( new PropertyF( it.hObj() ) );
6890  std::string parentName( it.parent().name() );
6891  if( parentName.find( "Gain" ) == 0 )
6892  {
6893  // remove the 'Gain' to get the original string from the selector the user would expect!
6894  parentName = parentName.substr( 4 );
6895  }
6896  m_chunkGainString2IndexMap.insert( std::make_pair( parentName, static_cast<unsigned int>( m_chunkGains.size() - 1 ) ) );
6897  }
6898  }
6899  break;
6900  default:
6901  break;
6902  }
6903  ++it;
6904  }
6905  }
6906  void collectSelectedChunkFeatures( ComponentIterator it )
6907  {
6908  if( m_chunkCounterValues.empty() && m_chunkTimerValues.empty() && m_chunkGains.empty() )
6909  {
6910  collectChunkFeatures( it );
6911  }
6912  }
6913  }* m_pRefData;
6914 #endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
6915 private:
6916  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6917  void bindPublicProperties( void )
6918  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6919  {
6920  DeviceComponentLocator locator( getComponentLocator() );
6921  locator.bindComponent( requestResult, "Result" );
6922  locator.bindComponent( requestState, "State" );
6923  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "Info" );
6924  m_pRefData->m_infoIterator = ComponentIterator( locator.searchbase_id() );
6925  m_pRefData->m_infoIterator = m_pRefData->m_infoIterator.firstChild();
6926  locator.bindComponent( infoFrameID, "FrameID" );
6927  locator.bindComponent( infoFrameNr, "FrameNr" );
6928  locator.bindComponent( infoExposeStart_us, "ExposeStart_us" );
6929  locator.bindComponent( infoExposeTime_us, "ExposeTime_us" );
6930  locator.bindComponent( infoTransferDelay_us, "TransferDelay_us" );
6931  locator.bindComponent( infoGain_dB, "Gain_dB" );
6932  locator.bindComponent( infoTimeStamp_us, "TimeStamp_us" );
6933  locator.bindComponent( infoSettingUsed, "SettingUsed" );
6934  locator.bindComponent( infoImageAverage, "ImageAverage" );
6935  locator.bindComponent( infoVideoChannel, "VideoChannel" );
6936  locator.bindComponent( infoCameraOutputUsed, "CameraOutputUsed" );
6937  locator.bindComponent( infoLineCounter, "LineCounter" );
6938  locator.bindComponent( infoMissingData_pc, "MissingData_pc" );
6939  locator.bindComponent( infoIOStatesAtExposureStart, "IOStatesAtExposureStart" );
6940  locator.bindComponent( infoIOStatesAtExposureEnd, "IOStatesAtExposureEnd" );
6941  HLIST hList = locator.findComponent( "ChunkData" );
6942  if( hList != INVALID_ID )
6943  {
6944  ComponentLocator chunkFeatureLocator( hList );
6945  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkOffsetX, "ChunkOffsetX" );
6946  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkOffsetY, "ChunkOffsetY" );
6947  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkWidth, "ChunkWidth" );
6948  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkHeight, "ChunkHeight" );
6949  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkPixelFormat, "ChunkPixelFormat" );
6950  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkDynamicRangeMin, "ChunkDynamicRangeMin" );
6951  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkDynamicRangeMax, "ChunkDynamicRangeMax" );
6952  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkExposureTime, "ChunkExposureTime" );
6953  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkTimestamp, "ChunkTimestamp" );
6954  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkLineStatusAll, "ChunkLineStatusAll" );
6955  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkSequencerSetActive, "ChunkSequencerSetActive" );
6956  chunkFeatureLocator.bindComponent( chunkmvCustomIdentifier, "ChunkmvCustomIdentifier" );
6957  m_pRefData->collectSelectedChunkFeatures( ComponentIterator( hList ).firstChild() );
6958  }
6959  hList = locator.findComponent( "ImageProcessingResults" );
6960  if( hList != INVALID_ID )
6961  {
6962  m_pRefData->m_info_imageProcessingResultsIterator = ComponentIterator( hList ).firstChild();
6963  }
6964  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.hObj(), "Image" );
6965  locator.bindComponent( imageMemoryMode, "MemoryMode" );
6966  locator.bindComponent( imagePixelFormat, "PixelFormat" );
6967  locator.bindComponent( imageData, "Data" );
6968  locator.bindComponent( imageSize, "Size" );
6969  locator.bindComponent( imageFooter, "Footer" );
6970  locator.bindComponent( imageFooterSize, "FooterSize" );
6971  locator.bindComponent( imagePixelPitch, "PixelPitch" );
6972  locator.bindComponent( imageChannelCount, "ChannelCount" );
6973  locator.bindComponent( imageChannelOffset, "ChannelOffset" );
6974  locator.bindComponent( imageChannelBitDepth, "ChannelBitDepth" );
6975  locator.bindComponent( imageLinePitch, "LinePitch" );
6976  locator.bindComponent( imageChannelDesc, "ChannelDesc" );
6977  locator.bindComponent( imageBytesPerPixel, "BytesPerPixel" );
6978  locator.bindComponent( imageOffsetX, "OffsetX" );
6979  locator.bindComponent( imageOffsetY, "OffsetY" );
6980  locator.bindComponent( imageWidth, "Width" );
6981  locator.bindComponent( imageWidthTotal, "WidthTotal" );

6985  }
6986  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6987  void dealloc( void )
6988  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6989  {
6990  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
6991  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
6992  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
6993  {
6994  delete m_pRefData;
6995  m_pRefData = 0;
6996  }
6997  }

8366 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8368 
8471 class FunctionInterface
8472 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8473 {
8474  typedef std::vector<Request*> RequestVector;
8475 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
8476  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8477  struct ReferenceCountedData
8478  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8479  {
8480  ComponentList m_requestList;
8481  ComponentList m_imageRequestControlList;
8482  mutable std::vector<std::string> m_imageRequestControls;
8483  mutable RequestVector m_requests;
8484  Request* m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout;
8485  mutable std::vector<std::string> m_settings;
8486  mutable unsigned int m_lastImageRequestChangedCounter;
8487  mutable unsigned int m_lastSettingsListChangedCounter;
8488  Device* m_pDevice;
8489  RequestFactory* m_pRequestFactory;
8490  PropertyI m_requestCount;
8491  PropertyI m_captureBufferAlignment;
8492  ComponentList m_settingsList;
8493  unsigned int m_refCnt;
8494  ReferenceCountedData( Device* pDev, RequestFactory* pRequestFactory ) : m_requestList(), m_imageRequestControlList(),
8495  m_imageRequestControls(), m_requests(), m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout( 0 ), m_settings(), m_lastImageRequestChangedCounter( 0 ),
8496  m_lastSettingsListChangedCounter( 0 ), m_pDevice( pDev ), m_pRequestFactory( pRequestFactory ),
8497  m_requestCount(), m_captureBufferAlignment(), m_settingsList(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
8498  // make sure there are NO assignments or copy constructions by accident!
8499  ReferenceCountedData& operator=( const ReferenceCountedData& rhs );
8500  ReferenceCountedData( const ReferenceCountedData& src );
8501  ~ReferenceCountedData()
8502  {
8503  RequestVector::size_type rvSize = m_requests.size();
8504  for( RequestVector::size_type i = 0; i < rvSize; i++ )
8505  {
8506  delete m_requests[i];
8507  }
8508  delete m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout;
8509  }
8510  }* m_pRefData;
8511 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
8512  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8513  Request* createRequest( int requestNr ) const
8514  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8515  {
8516  if( m_pRefData->m_pRequestFactory )
8517  {
8518  return m_pRefData->m_pRequestFactory->createRequest( m_pRefData->m_pDevice, requestNr );
8519  }
8520  return new Request( m_pRefData->m_pDevice, requestNr );
8521  }
8522  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8523  void dealloc( void )
8524  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8525  {
8526  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
8527  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
8528  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
8529  {
8530  delete m_pRefData;
8531  m_pRefData = 0;
8532  }
8533  }
8534  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8535  void updateRequests( void ) const
8536  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8537  {
8538  RequestVector::size_type rListSize = static_cast<RequestVector::size_type>( m_pRefData->m_requestList.size() );
8539  RequestVector::size_type vSize = m_pRefData->m_requests.size();
8540  if( rListSize < vSize )
8541  {
8542  // requests have been deleted...
8543  for( RequestVector::size_type i = rListSize; i < vSize; i++ )
8544  {
8545  delete m_pRefData->m_requests[i];
8546  }
8547  m_pRefData->m_requests.resize( rListSize );
8548  }
8549  else if( rListSize > vSize )
8550  {
8551  // there are new requests
8552  ComponentIterator it( m_pRefData->m_requestList );
8553  it = it.firstChild();
8554  for( RequestVector::size_type i = 0; ( i < vSize ) && it.isValid(); i++ )
8555  {
8556  ++it;
8557  }
8558  while( it.isValid() )
8559  {
8560  // this might happen, if there are several instances referring to the same device
8561  // and another instance has created new requests in the meantime, or if this instance
8562  // has just been created
8563  m_pRefData->m_requests.push_back( createRequest( static_cast<int>( m_pRefData->m_requests.size() ) ) );
8564  ++it;
8565  }
8566  }
8567  }
8568  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8569  void updateSettings( void ) const
8570  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8571  {
8572  unsigned int actChangedCounter = m_pRefData->m_settingsList.changedCounter();
8573  if( m_pRefData->m_lastSettingsListChangedCounter != actChangedCounter )
8574  {
8575  // something has changed in the settings list -> update the string array
8576  // the string array must be filled from scratch each time because settings might have been
8577  // deleted as well...
8578  m_pRefData->m_settings.clear();
8579  ComponentIterator it( m_pRefData->m_settingsList );
8580  it = it.firstChild();
8581  while( it.isValid() )
8582  {
8583  // this might happen, if there are several instances referring to the same device
8584  // and another instance has created new settings in the meantime, or if this instance
8585  // has just been created
8586  m_pRefData->m_settings.push_back( it.name() );
8587  ++it;
8588  }
8589  m_pRefData->m_lastSettingsListChangedCounter = actChangedCounter;
8590  }
8591  }
8592  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8593  void updateImageRequestControls( void ) const
8594  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8595  {
8596  unsigned int actChangedCounter = m_pRefData->m_imageRequestControlList.changedCounter();
8597  if( m_pRefData->m_lastImageRequestChangedCounter != actChangedCounter )
8598  {
8599  // something has changed in the image request controls list -> update the string array
8600  // the string array must be filled from scratch each time because objects might have been
8601  // deleted as well...
8602  m_pRefData->m_imageRequestControls.clear();
8603  ComponentIterator it( m_pRefData->m_imageRequestControlList );
8604  it = it.firstChild();
8605  while( it.isValid() )
8606  {
8607  // this might happen, if there are several instances referring to the same device
8608  // and another instance has created new object in the meantime, or if this instance
8609  // has just been created
8610  m_pRefData->m_imageRequestControls.push_back( it.name() );
8611  ++it;
8612  }
8613  m_pRefData->m_lastImageRequestChangedCounter = actChangedCounter;
8614  }
8615  }
8616 public:
8618 
8628  explicit FunctionInterface(
8631  Device* pDev,
8636  RequestFactory* pRequestFactory = 0 ) : m_pRefData( 0 )
8637  {
8638  if( !pDev->isOpen() )
8639  {
8640  pDev->open();
8641  }
8642  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData( pDev, pRequestFactory );
8643  DeviceComponentLocator locator( pDev, dltSetting );
8644  m_pRefData->m_settingsList = ComponentList( locator.searchbase_id() );
8645  locator.bindSearchBaseList( pDev, dltRequest );
8646  m_pRefData->m_requestList = ComponentList( locator.searchbase_id() );
8647  locator.bindSearchBaseList( pDev, dltRequestCtrl );
8648  m_pRefData->m_imageRequestControlList = ComponentList( locator.searchbase_id() );
8649  locator.bindSearchBaseList( pDev, dltSystemSettings );
8650  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_requestCount, "RequestCount" );
8651  locator.bindSearchBaseList( pDev, dltInfo );
8652  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_captureBufferAlignment, "CaptureBufferAlignment" );
8653  updateRequests();
8654  locator.bindSearchBaseList( pDev, dltInfo );
8655  if( locator.findComponent( "CurrentRequestLayout" ) != INVALID_ID )
8656  {
8657  m_pRefData->m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout = createRequest( -1 );
8658  }
8659  }
8661  explicit FunctionInterface(
8663  const FunctionInterface& src ) : m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData )
8664  {
8665  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
8666  }
8668  virtual ~FunctionInterface( void )
8669  {
8670  dealloc();
8671  }
8672 #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
8673  FunctionInterface& operator=( const FunctionInterface& rhs )
8675  {
8676  if( this != &rhs )
8677  {
8678  dealloc();
8679  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
8680  // inc. the NEW reference count
8681  ++m_pRefData->m_refCnt;
8682  }
8683  return *this;
8684  }
8685 #endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
8686 
8712  int acquisitionStart( void ) const
8713  {
8714  return DMR_AcquisitionStart( m_pRefData->m_pDevice->hDrv() );
8715  }
8717 
8738  int acquisitionStop( void ) const
8739  {
8740  return DMR_AcquisitionStop( m_pRefData->m_pDevice->hDrv() );
8741  }
8743 
8760  int createImageRequestControl(
8762  const std::string& name,
8764  const std::string& parent = "Base",
8767  ComponentList* pNewRequestControl = 0 )
8768  {
8769  HLIST newID;
8770  int result = DMR_CreateRequestControl( m_pRefData->m_pDevice->hDrv(), name.c_str(), parent.c_str(), &newID, 0 );
8771  if( pNewRequestControl )
8772  {
8773  *pNewRequestControl = ComponentList( newID );
8774  }
8775  return result;
8776  }
8778 
8804  int createSetting(
8806  const std::string& name,
8808  const std::string& parent = "Base",
8811  ComponentList* pNewSetting = 0 )
8812  {
8813  HLIST newID = INVALID_ID;
8814  int result = DMR_CreateSetting( m_pRefData->m_pDevice->hDrv(), name.c_str(), parent.c_str(), &newID );
8815  updateSettings();
8816  if( pNewSetting )
8817  {
8818  if( newID == INVALID_ID )
8819  {
8820  *pNewSetting = ComponentList();
8821  }
8822  else
8823  {
8824  *pNewSetting = ComponentList( newID );
8825  }
8826  }
8827  return result;
8828  }

8844  }

8876  }
8878 
8886  ComponentList getSetting(
8888  const std::string& name ) const
8889  {
8890  ComponentIterator it( m_pRefData->m_settingsList );
8891  it = it.firstChild();
8892  while( it.isValid() )
8893  {
8894  if( name == it.name() )
8895  {
8896  return ComponentList( it );
8897  }
8898  ++it;
8899  }
8900  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, PROPHANDLING_COMPONENT_NOT_FOUND, INVALID_ID, "Setting '" + name + "' could not be found" );
8901  return ComponentList();
8902  }

9203 
9219  int getCurrentCaptureBufferLayout(
9224  ImageRequestControl& imageRequestControl,
9228  Request** ppRequest = 0,
9232  int* pAlignment = 0 ) const
9233  {
9234  int result = DMR_NO_ERROR;
9235  if( ppRequest )
9236  {
9237  if( !m_pRefData->m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout )
9238  {
9239  // This feature is available for every driver, but could not be detected thus an
9240  // update might be required.
9241  return DMR_NEWER_LIBRARY_REQUIRED;
9242  }
9243  const TImageRequestControlMode previousMode( imageRequestControl.mode.read() );
9244  if( previousMode != ircmUpdateBufferLayout )
9245  {
9246  imageRequestControl.mode.write( ircmUpdateBufferLayout );
9247  }
9248  result = imageRequestSingle( &imageRequestControl );
9249  if( previousMode != ircmUpdateBufferLayout )
9250  {
9251  imageRequestControl.mode.write( previousMode );
9252  }
9253  *ppRequest = m_pRefData->m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout;
9254  }
9255  if( pAlignment )
9256  {
9257  *pAlignment = m_pRefData->m_captureBufferAlignment.read();
9258  }
9259  return result;
9260  }
9262 
9278  int getCurrentCaptureBufferLayout(
9283  ImageRequestControl& imageRequestControl,
9287  int& size,
9291  int& alignment ) const
9292  {
9293  Request* pRequest = 0;
9294  int result = getCurrentCaptureBufferLayout( imageRequestControl, &pRequest, &alignment );
9295  if( m_pRefData->m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout )
9296  {
9297  size = m_pRefData->m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout->imageSize.read() + m_pRefData->m_pCurrentCaptureBufferLayout->imageFooterSize.read();
9298  }
9299  else
9300  {
9301  size = 0;
9302  }
9303  return result;
9304  }
9306 
9311  bool isRequestNrValid( int nr ) const
9312  {
9313  if( nr < 0 )
9314  {
9315  return false;
9316  }
9317 
9318  if( nr >= static_cast<int>( m_pRefData->m_requests.size() ) )
9319  {
9320  updateRequests();
9321  }
9322 
9323  return nr < static_cast<int>( m_pRefData->m_requests.size() );
9324  }

10369 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10371 
10376 class ImageProcessing : public ComponentCollection
10377 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10378 {
10379  typedef std::vector<GainOffsetKneeChannelParameters*> GainOffsetKneeParameterContainer;
10380  typedef std::vector<LUTParameters*> LUTParameterContainer;
10381  typedef std::vector<MirrorParameters*> MirrorParameterContainer;
10382  typedef std::vector<WhiteBalanceSettings*> WBSettingsContainer;
10383 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
10384  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10385  struct ReferenceCountedData
10386  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10387  {
10388  GainOffsetKneeParameterContainer m_GainOffsetKneeParameters;
10389  LUTParameterContainer m_LUTParameters;
10390  MirrorParameterContainer m_MirrorParameters;
10391  WBSettingsContainer m_WBUserSettings;
10392  unsigned int m_refCnt;
10393  ReferenceCountedData() : m_GainOffsetKneeParameters(), m_LUTParameters(),
10394  m_MirrorParameters(), m_WBUserSettings(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
10395  ~ReferenceCountedData()
10396  {
10397  const GainOffsetKneeParameterContainer::size_type GainOffsetKneeParameterCnt = m_GainOffsetKneeParameters.size();
10398  for( GainOffsetKneeParameterContainer::size_type h = 0; h < GainOffsetKneeParameterCnt; h++ )
10399  {
10400  delete m_GainOffsetKneeParameters[h];
10401  }
10402  const LUTParameterContainer::size_type LUTParametersCnt = m_LUTParameters.size();
10403  for( LUTParameterContainer::size_type i = 0; i < LUTParametersCnt; i++ )
10404  {
10405  delete m_LUTParameters[i];
10406  }
10407  const MirrorParameterContainer::size_type MirrorParametersCnt = m_MirrorParameters.size();
10408  for( MirrorParameterContainer::size_type j = 0; j < MirrorParametersCnt; j++ )
10409  {
10410  delete m_MirrorParameters[j];
10411  }
10412  const WBSettingsContainer::size_type WBSettingsCnt = m_WBUserSettings.size();
10413  for( WBSettingsContainer::size_type k = 0; k < WBSettingsCnt; k++ )
10414  {
10415  delete m_WBUserSettings[k];
10416  }
10417  }
10418  }* m_pRefData;
10419 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
10420  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10421  void bindPublicProperties( void )
10422  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10423  {

10535  void dealloc( void )
10536  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
10537  {
10538  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
10539  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
10540  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
10541  {
10542  delete m_pRefData;
10543  m_pRefData = 0;
10544  }
10545  }

10575  {

10577  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData();
10578  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "ImageProcessing" );
10579  m_hRoot = locator.searchbase_id();
10580  bindPublicProperties();
10581  int number = 1;
10582  HOBJ hList = INVALID_ID;
10583  // create the WB user parameter objects for this setting
10584  do
10585  {
10586  std::ostringstream oss;
10587  oss << "WhiteBalanceSettings-" << number++;
10588  if( ( hList = locator.findComponent( oss.str() ) ) != INVALID_ID )
10589  {
10590  m_pRefData->m_WBUserSettings.push_back( new WhiteBalanceSettings( hList ) );
10591  }
10592  }
10593  while( hList != INVALID_ID );
10594 
10595  // create the GainOffsetKnee parameter objects for this setting
10596  if( locator.findComponent( "GainOffsetKnee" ) != INVALID_ID )
10597  {
10598  // this driver offers GainOffsetKnee support
10599  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "GainOffsetKnee" );
10600  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "GainOffsetKneeChannels" );
10601  number = 0;
10602  do
10603  {
10604  std::ostringstream oss;
10605  oss << "Channel-" << number++;
10606  if( ( hList = locator.findComponent( oss.str() ) ) != INVALID_ID )
10607  {
10608  m_pRefData->m_GainOffsetKneeParameters.push_back( new GainOffsetKneeChannelParameters( hList ) );
10609  }
10610  }
10611  while( hList != INVALID_ID );
10612  }
10613 
10614  locator.bindSearchBase( m_hRoot );
10615  // create the Mirror parameter objects for this setting
10616  if( locator.findComponent( "Mirror" ) != INVALID_ID )
10617  {
10618  // this driver offers Mirror support
10619  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "Mirror" );
10620  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "MirrorChannels" );
10621  number = 0;
10622  do
10623  {
10624  std::ostringstream oss;
10625  oss << "Channel-" << number++;
10626  if( ( hList = locator.findComponent( oss.str() ) ) != INVALID_ID )
10627  {
10628  m_pRefData->m_MirrorParameters.push_back( new MirrorParameters( hList ) );
10629  }
10630  }

10708  {

10712  dealloc();

10714  ++m_pRefData->m_refCnt;
10715  bindPublicProperties();
10716  }
10717  return *this;
10718  }

11182  void setSaturation(
11184  double K )
11185  {
11186  std::vector<double> row( 3, 0. );
11187  row[0] = 0.299 + 0.701 * K;
11188  row[1] = 0.587 * ( 1 - K );
11189  row[2] = 0.114 * ( 1 - K );
11190  colorTwistRow0.write( row, true );
11191  row[0] = 0.299 * ( 1 - K );
11192  row[1] = 0.587 + 0.413 * K;
11193  row[2] = 0.114 * ( 1 - K );
11194  colorTwistRow1.write( row, true );
11195  row[0] = 0.299 * ( 1 - K );
11196  row[1] = 0.587 * ( 1 - K );
11197  row[2] = 0.114 + 0.886 * K;
11198  colorTwistRow2.write( row, true );
11199  }

12537 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12539 
12640 class RTCtrProgram : public ComponentCollection
12641 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12642 {
12643  friend class IOSubSystem;
12644  typedef std::vector<RTCtrProgramStep*> RTCtrlProgramStepVector;
12645 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
12646  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12647  struct ReferenceCountedData
12648  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12649  {
12650  HDRV m_hDrv;
12651  mutable RTCtrlProgramStepVector m_programSteps;
12652  PropertyI m_programSize;
12653  HLIST m_hRTCtrList;
12654  HOBJ m_programStepList;
12655  unsigned int m_refCnt;
12656  ReferenceCountedData( HDRV hDrv, HLIST hList ) : m_hDrv( hDrv ), m_programSteps(), m_programSize(),
12657  m_hRTCtrList( hList ), m_programStepList(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
12658  ~ReferenceCountedData()
12659  {
12660  RTCtrlProgramStepVector::size_type vSize = m_programSteps.size();
12661  for( RTCtrlProgramStepVector::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
12662  {
12663  delete m_programSteps[i];
12664  }
12665  }
12666  }* m_pRefData;
12667 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
12668  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12669  void bindPublicProperties( HLIST hList )
12670  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12671  {
12672  ComponentLocator locator( hList );
12673  locator.bindComponent( mode, "Mode" );
12674  locator.bindComponent( filename, "Filename" );
12675  locator.bindComponent( programState, "ProgramState" );
12676  }
12677  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12678  void dealloc( void )
12679  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12680  {
12681  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
12682  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
12683  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
12684  {
12685  delete m_pRefData;
12686  m_pRefData = 0;
12687  }
12688  }
12689  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12690  void updateProgram( void ) const
12691  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12692  {
12693  RTCtrlProgramStepVector::size_type vSize = m_pRefData->m_programSteps.size();
12694  unsigned int lSize = ComponentList( m_pRefData->m_programStepList ).size();
12695  if( lSize < vSize )
12696  {
12697  // steps have been deleted somewhere...
12698  for( unsigned int i = lSize; i < vSize; i++ )
12699  {
12700  delete m_pRefData->m_programSteps[i];
12701  }
12702  m_pRefData->m_programSteps.resize( lSize );
12703  }
12704  else if( lSize > vSize )
12705  {
12706  // new steps have been created
12707  ComponentIterator iter( m_pRefData->m_programStepList );
12708  iter = iter.firstChild();
12709  // move to the next valid end point
12710  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
12711  {
12712  ++iter;
12713  }
12714 
12715  while( iter.isValid() )
12716  {
12717  m_pRefData->m_programSteps.push_back( new RTCtrProgramStep( iter ) );
12718  ++iter;
12719  }
12720  }
12721  }
12722  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12723  explicit RTCtrProgram( HDRV hDrv, HLIST hList ) : ComponentCollection( hList ),
12724  m_pRefData( new ReferenceCountedData( hDrv, hList ) ), mode(), filename(), programState()
12725  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
12726  {
12727  ComponentLocator locator( hList );
12728  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_programSize, "ProgramSize" );
12729  bindPublicProperties( m_pRefData->m_hRTCtrList );
12730  m_pRefData->m_programStepList = locator.findComponent( "RTCtrProgram" );
12731  updateProgram();
12732  }
12733 public:
12735  explicit RTCtrProgram(
12737  const RTCtrProgram& src ) : ComponentCollection( src.m_hRoot ), m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData ), mode( src.mode ),
12738  filename( src.filename ), programState( src.programState )
12739  {
12740  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
12741  }
12743  ~RTCtrProgram()
12744  {
12745  dealloc();
12746  }
12747 # ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
12748  RTCtrProgram& operator=( const RTCtrProgram& rhs )
12750  {
12751  if( this != &rhs )
12752  {
12753  dealloc();
12754  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
12755  // inc. the NEW reference count
12756  ++m_pRefData->m_refCnt;
12757  bindPublicProperties( m_pRefData->m_hRTCtrList );
12758  }
12759  return *this;
12760  }
12761 # endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
12762  void setProgramSize(
12765  int newSize )
12766  {
12767  m_pRefData->m_programSize.write( newSize );
12768  updateProgram();
12769  }
12771 
12774  int getProgramSize( void ) const
12775  {
12776  return m_pRefData->m_programSize.read();
12777  }
12779 
12787  RTCtrProgramStep* programStep(
12789  unsigned int nr ) const
12790  {
12791  updateProgram();
12792  return m_pRefData->m_programSteps.at( nr );
12793  }
12794  PYTHON_ONLY( %immutable; )
12796 
12803  PropertyIRTCtrlModes mode;
12805 
12811  PropertyS filename;
12813  PropertyS programState;
12814  PYTHON_ONLY( %mutable; )
12816 
12824  int load( void )
12825  {
12826  return DMR_LoadRTCtrProgram( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, m_pRefData->m_hRTCtrList );
12827  }
12829 
12837  int save( void )
12838  {
12839  return DMR_SaveRTCtrProgram( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, m_pRefData->m_hRTCtrList );
12840  }
12841 };

13265 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
13266 # if !defined(WRAP_PYTHON) // To date, no customer uses Python, so we don't need backward compatibility here.
13267 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13268 inline const EventData& Event::getData( void ) const
13269 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13270 {
13271  TDMR_ERROR result = DMR_NO_ERROR;
13272  if( ( result = DMR_EventGetData( m_hDrv, m_type, 0, 0, &m_data, sizeof( m_data ) ) ) != DMR_NO_ERROR )
13273  {
13274  std::ostringstream oss;
13275  oss << "Couldn't obtain event data for event type " << m_type << "(string representation: " << type.name() << ")";
13276  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID, oss.str() );
13277  }
13278  return m_data;
13279 }

13281 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13282 inline EventWaitResults::EventWaitResults( int errorCode, TDeviceEventType waitMask, TDeviceEventType resultMask ) : m_errorCode( errorCode ), m_waitMask( waitMask ), m_resultMask( resultMask ) {}
13283 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13284 
13285 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13286 inline EventSubSystem::EventSubSystem( Device* pDev ) : m_pRefData( 0 )
13287 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13288 {
13289  if( !pDev->isOpen() )
13290  {
13291  pDev->open();
13292  }
13293 
13294  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData( pDev->hDrv() );
13295 
13296  TDMR_ERROR result;
13297  HLIST hList;
13298  if( ( result = DMR_FindList( pDev->hDrv(), 0, dmltEventSubSystemSettings, 0, &hList ) ) == DMR_NO_ERROR )
13299  {
13300  ComponentIterator it( hList );
13301  it = it.firstChild();
13302  while( it.isValid() )
13303  {
13304  Event* p = new Event( pDev->hDrv(), it.hObj() );
13305  m_pRefData->m_mTypeToEvent.insert( std::make_pair( p->type.read(), p ) );
13306  m_pRefData->m_mNameToEvent.insert( std::make_pair( p->type.readS(), p ) );
13307  m_pRefData->m_vEvents.push_back( p );
13308  ++it;
13309  }
13310  }
13311 }
13312 
13313 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13314 inline EventWaitResults EventSubSystem::waitFor( int timeout_ms, TDeviceEventType mask )
13315 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13316 {
13317  TDeviceEventType resultMask;
13318  int errorCode = DMR_EventWaitFor( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, timeout_ms, mask, 0, 0, &resultMask );
13319  return EventWaitResults( errorCode, mask, resultMask );
13320 }

13459 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13461 
13470 class IOSubSystem
13471 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13472 {
13473 protected:
13474 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
13475  typedef std::vector<RTCtrProgram*> RTCtrProgramVector;
13476  typedef std::vector<DigitalInput*> DigitalInputVector;
13477  typedef std::vector<DigitalOutput*> DigitalOutputVector;
13478  typedef std::vector<SyncOutput*> SyncOutputVector;
13479  typedef std::vector<PulseStartConfiguration*> PulseStartConfigurationVector;
13480  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13481  struct ReferenceCountedData
13482  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13483  {
13484  HDRV m_hDrv;
13485  DigitalInputVector m_vInputs;
13486  DigitalOutputVector m_vOutputs;
13487  SyncOutputVector m_vHDOutputs;
13488  SyncOutputVector m_vVDOutputs;
13489  mutable RTCtrProgramVector m_RTCtrPrograms;
13490  PulseStartConfigurationVector m_PulseStartConfigurations;
13491  unsigned int m_refCnt;
13492  ReferenceCountedData( HDRV hDrv ) : m_hDrv( hDrv ), m_vInputs(), m_vOutputs(),
13493  m_vHDOutputs(), m_vVDOutputs(), m_RTCtrPrograms(), m_PulseStartConfigurations(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
13494  ~ReferenceCountedData()
13495  {
13496  DigitalInputVector::size_type vInputsSize = m_vInputs.size();
13497  for( DigitalInputVector::size_type i = 0; i < vInputsSize; i++ )
13498  {
13499  delete m_vInputs[i];
13500  }
13501 
13502  DigitalOutputVector::size_type vOutputsSize = m_vOutputs.size();
13503  for( DigitalOutputVector::size_type j = 0; j < vOutputsSize; j++ )
13504  {
13505  delete m_vOutputs[j];
13506  }
13507 
13508  SyncOutputVector::size_type vSyncOutputsSize = m_vHDOutputs.size();
13509  for( SyncOutputVector::size_type k = 0; k < vSyncOutputsSize; k++ )
13510  {
13511  delete m_vHDOutputs[k];
13512  }
13513 
13514  vSyncOutputsSize = m_vVDOutputs.size();
13515  for( SyncOutputVector::size_type l = 0; l < vSyncOutputsSize; l++ )
13516  {
13517  delete m_vVDOutputs[l];
13518  }
13519 
13520  RTCtrProgramVector::size_type vRTCProgSize = m_RTCtrPrograms.size();
13521  for( RTCtrProgramVector::size_type m = 0; m < vRTCProgSize; m++ )
13522  {
13523  delete m_RTCtrPrograms[m];
13524  }
13525 
13526  PulseStartConfigurationVector::size_type vPulseStartConfigurationsSize = m_PulseStartConfigurations.size();
13527  for( PulseStartConfigurationVector::size_type n = 0; n < vPulseStartConfigurationsSize; n++ )
13528  {
13529  delete m_PulseStartConfigurations[n];
13530  }
13531  }
13532  }* m_pRefData;
13533  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

13535  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13536  {
13537  if( !pDev->isOpen() )
13538  {
13539  pDev->open();
13540  }
13541  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData( pDev->hDrv() );
13542  }

13545  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

13549  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
13550  {
13551  delete m_pRefData;
13552  m_pRefData = 0;
13553  }

13564  registerRTCtrProgram( hDrv, hList );
13565  }
13566  }
13567  }
