13814 class IOSubSystemBlueFOX : public IOSubSystem
13815 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
13816 {
13817 private:
13818  unsigned int readRegister( const PropertyI& reg ) const
13819  {
13820  std::vector<int> v;
13821  reg.read( v );
13822  std::vector<int>::size_type vSize = v.size();
13823  unsigned int result = 0;
13824  for( std::vector<int>::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
13825  {
13826  result |= ( ( v[i] & 1 ) << i );
13827  }
13828  return result;
13829  }
13830  unsigned int readRegisterAtomic( const PropertyI& reg ) const
13831  {
13832  std::vector<int> v;
13833  reg.read( v, true );
13834  std::vector<int>::size_type vSize = v.size();
13835  unsigned int result = 0;
13836  for( std::vector<int>::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
13837  {
13838  result |= ( ( v[i] & 1 ) << i );
13839  }
13840  return result;
13841  }
13842  PropertyI m_inputRegister;
13843  PropertyI m_outputRegister;
13844 public:
13846  explicit IOSubSystemBlueFOX(
13848  Device* pDev ) : IOSubSystem( pDev ), m_inputRegister(), m_outputRegister(), digitalInputThreshold()
13849  {
13850  DeviceComponentLocator locator( pDev, dltIOSubSystem );
13851  locator.bindComponent( digitalInputThreshold, "DigitalInputThreshold" );
13852  locator.bindComponent( m_inputRegister, "DigitalInputs" );
13853  locator.bindComponent( m_outputRegister, "DigitalOutputs" );
13854 
13855  // register all input pins
13856  unsigned int pinCount = m_inputRegister.valCount();
13857  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < pinCount; i++ )
13858  {
13859  std::ostringstream oss;
13860  oss << "DigitialInput" << i;
13861  registerDigitalInput( pDev->hDrv(), m_inputRegister, i, oss.str() );
13862  }
13863 
13864  // register all output pins
13865  pinCount = m_outputRegister.valCount();
13866  for( unsigned int j = 0; j < pinCount; j++ )
13867  {
13868  std::ostringstream oss;
13869  oss << "DigitalOutput" << j;
13870  registerDigitalOutput( m_outputRegister, j, oss.str() );
13871  }
13872 
13873  registerAllRTCtrPrograms( pDev->hDrv(), locator.findComponent( "HardwareRealTimeController" ) );
13874  }
13876 
13885  virtual unsigned int readInputRegister( void ) const
13886  {
13887  const TDMR_ERROR result = DMR_UpdateDigitalInputs( m_pRefData->m_hDrv );
13888  if( result != DMR_NO_ERROR )
13889  {
13890  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID );
13891  }
13892  return readRegister( m_inputRegister );
13893  }
13895 
13904  unsigned int readInputRegisterAtomic( void ) const
13905  {
13906  const TDMR_ERROR result = DMR_UpdateDigitalInputs( m_pRefData->m_hDrv );
13907  if( result != DMR_NO_ERROR )
13908  {
13909  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID );
13910  }
13911  return readRegisterAtomic( m_inputRegister );
13912  }
13914 
13923  virtual unsigned int readOutputRegister( void ) const
13924  {
13925  return readRegister( m_outputRegister );
13926  }
13928 
13937  unsigned int readOutputRegisterAtomic( void ) const
13938  {
13939  return readRegisterAtomic( m_outputRegister );
13940  }
13942 
13956  void writeOutputRegister(
13958  unsigned int value,
13963  unsigned int mask = UINT_MAX )
13964  {
13965  unsigned int newVal = ( readRegister( m_outputRegister ) & ~mask ) | ( mask & value );
13966  DigitalOutputVector::size_type vSize = m_pRefData->m_vOutputs.size();
13967  std::vector<int> v( vSize );
13968  for( std::vector<int>::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
13969  {
13970  v[i] = ( ( newVal & ( 1 << i ) ) != 0 );
13971  }
13972  m_outputRegister.write( v );
13973  }
13975 
13989  void writeOutputRegisterAtomic(
13991  unsigned int value,
13996  unsigned int mask = UINT_MAX )
13997  {
13998  unsigned int newVal = ( readRegister( m_outputRegister ) & ~mask ) | ( mask & value );
13999  DigitalOutputVector::size_type vSize = m_pRefData->m_vOutputs.size();
14000  std::vector<int> v( vSize );
14001  for( std::vector<int>::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
14002  {
14003  v[i] = ( ( newVal & ( 1 << i ) ) != 0 );
14004  }
14005  m_outputRegister.write( v, true );
14006  }
14007  PYTHON_ONLY( %immutable; )
14009 
14018  PropertyIBlueFOXDigitalInputThreshold digitalInputThreshold;
14019  PYTHON_ONLY( %mutable; )

14074 class IOSubSystemCommon : public IOSubSystem
14075 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14076 {
14077  ComponentList m_inputs;
14078 public:
14080  explicit IOSubSystemCommon(
14082  Device* pDev ) : IOSubSystem( pDev ), m_inputs()
14083  {
14084  DeviceComponentLocator locator( pDev, dltIOSubSystem );
14085  HOBJ hObj = locator.findComponent( "PulseStartConfigurations" );
14086  if( hObj != INVALID_ID )
14087  {
14088  ComponentIterator itPulseConfigs( hObj );
14089  itPulseConfigs = itPulseConfigs.firstChild();
14090  while( itPulseConfigs.isValid() )
14091  {
14092  registerPulseStartConfiguration( itPulseConfigs.hObj() );
14093  ++itPulseConfigs;
14094  }
14095  }
14096 
14097  locator.bindComponent( m_inputs, "DigitalInputs", 0, 1 );
14098  if( m_inputs.isValid() )
14099  {
14100  ComponentIterator it( m_inputs );
14101  it = it.firstChild();
14102  while( it.isValid() )
14103  {
14104  registerDigitalInput( pDev->hDrv(), PropertyI( it ), 0, it.name() );
14105  ++it;
14106  }
14107  }
14108 
14109  ComponentList outputs;
14110  locator.bindComponent( outputs, "DigitalOutputs", 0, 1 );
14111  if( outputs.isValid() )
14112  {
14113  ComponentIterator it( outputs );
14114  it = it.firstChild();
14115  while( it.isValid() )
14116  {
14117  if( it.isList() )
14118  {
14119  ComponentLocator outputStateLocator( it );
14120  registerDigitalOutput( PropertyI( outputStateLocator.findComponent( "State" ) ), 0, it.name() );
14121  }
14122  ++it;
14123  }
14124  }
14125 
14126  registerAllRTCtrPrograms( pDev->hDrv(), locator.findComponent( "HardwareRealTimeController" ) );
14127  }
14129 
14141  virtual unsigned int readInputRegister( void ) const
14142  {
14143  DMR_UpdateDigitalInputs( m_pRefData->m_hDrv );
14144  if( !m_inputs.isValid() )
14145  {
14146  return 0;
14147  }
14148  unsigned int result = 0;
14149  ComponentIterator it( m_inputs );
14150  int i = 0;
14151  it = it.firstChild();
14152  while( it.isValid() )
14153  {
14154  PropertyI input( it );
14155  result |= ( ( input.read() & 1 ) << i );
14156  ++it;
14157  ++i;
14158  }
14159  return result;
14160  }
14162 
14174  virtual unsigned int readOutputRegister( void ) const
14175  {
14176  unsigned int result = 0;
14177  DigitalOutputVector::size_type vSize = m_pRefData->m_vOutputs.size();
14178  for( DigitalOutputVector::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
14179  {
14180  result |= ( ( m_pRefData->m_vOutputs[i]->get() & 1 ) << i );
14181  }
14182  return result;
14183  }
14185 
14199  void writeOutputRegister(
14201  unsigned int value,
14206  unsigned int mask = UINT_MAX )
14207  {
14208  DigitalOutputVector::size_type vSize = m_pRefData->m_vOutputs.size();
14209  for( DigitalOutputVector::size_type i = 0; i < vSize; i++ )
14210  {
14211  if( mask & ( 1 << i ) )
14212  {
14213  if( value & ( 1 << i ) )
14214  {
14215  m_pRefData->m_vOutputs[i]->set();
14216  }
14217  else
14218  {
14219  m_pRefData->m_vOutputs[i]->reset();
14220  }
14221  }
14222  }
14223  }
14224 };

14242 class OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice
14243 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14244 {
14245 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
14246  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14247  struct OutputProperties
14248  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14249  {
14250  PropertyIDeviceDigitalOutputMode mode;
14251  PropertyIBoolean inverter;
14252  OutputProperties( HLIST hOutput ) : mode()
14253  {
14254  ComponentLocator locator( hOutput );
14255  locator.bindComponent( mode, "Mode" );
14256  locator.bindComponent( inverter, "Inverter" );
14257  }
14258  };
14259  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14260  struct ReferenceCountedData
14261  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14262  {
14263  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*> m_mOutputs;
14264  unsigned int m_refCnt;
14265  ReferenceCountedData() : m_mOutputs(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
14266  ~ReferenceCountedData()
14267  {
14268  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*>::iterator itEnd = m_mOutputs.end();
14269  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*>::iterator it = m_mOutputs.begin();
14270  while( it != itEnd )
14271  {
14272  delete it->second;
14273  ++it;
14274  }
14275  }
14276  }* m_pRefData;
14277  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14278  void dealloc( void )
14279  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14280  {
14281  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
14282  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
14283  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
14284  {
14285  delete m_pRefData;
14286  m_pRefData = 0;
14287  }
14288  }
14289  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14290  OutputProperties* getOutputProperties( DigitalOutput* pOutput ) const
14291  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14292  {
14293  if( pOutput )
14294  {
14295  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*>::iterator it = m_pRefData->m_mOutputs.find( pOutput->getDescription() );
14296  if( it != m_pRefData->m_mOutputs.end() )
14297  {
14298  return it->second;
14299  }
14300  }
14301  return 0;
14302  }
14303 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
14304 public:
14306  explicit OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice(
14308  Device* pDev ) : m_pRefData( 0 )
14309  {
14310  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData();
14311  DeviceComponentLocator locator( pDev, dltIOSubSystem );
14312  ComponentList outputs;
14313  locator.bindComponent( outputs, "DigitalOutputs" );
14314  if( outputs.isValid() )
14315  {
14316  ComponentIterator it( outputs.hObj() );
14317  it = it.firstChild();
14318  while( it.isValid() )
14319  {
14320  if( it.isList() )
14321  {
14322  m_pRefData->m_mOutputs.insert( std::pair<std::string, OutputProperties*>( it.name(), new OutputProperties( it ) ) );
14323  }
14324  ++it;
14325  }
14326  }
14327  }
14330  explicit OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice(
14332  const OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice& src ) : m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData )
14333  {
14334  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
14335  }
14337  ~OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice()
14338  {
14339  dealloc();
14340  }
14341 # ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
14342  OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice& operator=( const OutputSignalGeneratorBlueDevice& rhs )
14344  {

14346  {
14347  dealloc();
14348  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
14349  // inc. the NEW reference count
14350  ++m_pRefData->m_refCnt;
14351  }
14352  return *this;
14353  }
14354 # endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)

14365  int undefineSignal(
14369  DigitalOutput* pOutput )
14370  {
14371  if( !pOutput )
14372  {
14373  return DMR_INVALID_PARAMETER;
14374  }
14375  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14376  if( p )
14377  {
14378  p->mode.write( ddomManual );
14379  return DMR_NO_ERROR;
14380  }
14381  return DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE;
14382  }
14384  bool canCreateExposeActiveSignal(
14388  DigitalOutput* pOutput ) const
14389  {
14390  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14391  if( !p || !p->mode.isValid() )
14392  {
14393  return false;
14394  }
14395  unsigned int dictSize = p->mode.dictSize();
14396  for( unsigned int i = 0; i < dictSize; i++ )
14397  {
14398  if( p->mode.getTranslationDictValue( i ) == ddomExposureActive )
14399  {
14400  return true;
14401  }
14402  }
14403  return false;
14404  }
14406  bool canInvertSignal(
14410  DigitalOutput* pOutput ) const
14411  {
14412  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14413  return ( p && p->inverter.isValid() );
14414  }
14418  TDeviceDigitalOutputMode getOutputMode(
14422  DigitalOutput* pOutput ) const
14423  {
14424  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14425  if( !p )
14426  {
14427  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE, INVALID_ID, "Unsupported feature query(Could not obtain pointer to output properties)" );
14428  }
14429  return p->mode.read();
14430  }
14432  bool isOutputModeActive(
14436  DigitalOutput* pOutput,
14438  TDeviceDigitalOutputMode mode ) const
14439  {
14440  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14441  return ( p && p->mode.isValid() && ( p->mode.read() == mode ) );
14442  }
14444  bool isSignalInverted(
14448  DigitalOutput* pOutput ) const
14449  {
14450  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14451  return ( p && p->mode.isValid() && p->inverter.isValid() && ( p->inverter.read() == bTrue ) );
14452  }
14454 
14464  int setOutputMode(
14468  DigitalOutput* pOutput,
14471  TDeviceDigitalOutputMode mode,
14473  bool boInverted = false )
14474  {
14475  if( !pOutput )
14476  {
14477  return DMR_INVALID_PARAMETER;
14478  }
14479  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14480  if( p && p->mode.isValid() )
14481  {
14482  p->mode.write( mode );
14483  if( p->inverter.isValid() )
14484  {
14485  p->inverter.write( boInverted ? bTrue : bFalse );
14486  }
14487  else if( boInverted )
14488  {
14489  return DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE;
14490  }
14491  return DMR_NO_ERROR;
14492  }
14493  return DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE;
14494  }
14495 };

14629 
14732 class OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber
14733 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14734 {
14735 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
14736  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14737  struct OutputProperties
14738  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14739  {
14740  PropertyIDeviceDigitalOutputMode mode;
14741  PropertyI polarity;
14742  PropertyI delay_us;
14743  PropertyI width_us;
14744  PropertyI width_pclk;
14745  PropertyI startLevel;
14746  PropertyI polaritySwitchAfter_us;
14747  PropertyIDigitalSignal digitalSignal;
14748  PropertyI pulseStartConfiguration;
14749  OutputProperties( HLIST hOutput ) : mode(), polarity(), delay_us(), width_us(),
14750  width_pclk(), startLevel(), polaritySwitchAfter_us(), digitalSignal(),
14751  pulseStartConfiguration()
14752  {
14753  ComponentLocator locator( hOutput );
14754  locator.bindComponent( mode, "Mode" );
14755  locator.bindComponent( polarity, "Polarity" );
14756  locator.bindComponent( delay_us, "Delay_us" );
14757  locator.bindComponent( width_us, "Width_us" );
14758  locator.bindComponent( width_pclk, "Width_pclk" );
14759  locator.bindComponent( startLevel, "StartLevel" );
14760  locator.bindComponent( polaritySwitchAfter_us, "PolaritySwitchAfter_us" );
14761  locator.bindComponent( digitalSignal, "DigitalSignal" );
14762  locator.bindComponent( pulseStartConfiguration, "PulseStartConfiguration" );
14763  }
14764  };
14765  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14766  struct ReferenceCountedData
14767  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14768  {
14769  ComponentList m_outputs;
14770  PropertyIDeviceSignalOutputStartEvent m_pulseStartEventLineScan;
14771  PropertyI m_softwareSignalPeriod_pclk;
14772  PropertyI m_output;
14773  PropertyI m_width_pclk;
14774  PropertyI m_polarity;
14775  PropertyI m_divider;
14776  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*> m_mOutputs;
14777  unsigned int m_refCnt;
14778  ReferenceCountedData() : m_outputs(), m_pulseStartEventLineScan(),
14779  m_softwareSignalPeriod_pclk(), m_output(), m_width_pclk(),
14780  m_polarity(), m_divider(), m_mOutputs(), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
14781  ~ReferenceCountedData()
14782  {
14783  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*>::iterator itEnd = m_mOutputs.end();
14784  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*>::iterator it = m_mOutputs.begin();
14785  while( it != itEnd )
14786  {
14787  delete it->second;
14788  ++it;
14789  }
14790  }
14791  }* m_pRefData;
14792  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14793  void bindPublicProperties( HLIST hList )
14794  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14795  {
14796  ComponentLocator locator( hList );
14797  locator.bindComponent( controlMode, "ControlMode" );
14798  locator.bindComponent( pulseStartEvent, "PulseStartEvent" );
14799  locator.bindComponent( imageTrigger, "ImageTrigger" );
14800  }
14801  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14802  void dealloc( void )
14803  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14804  {
14805  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
14806  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
14807  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
14808  {
14809  delete m_pRefData;
14810  m_pRefData = 0;
14811  }
14812  }
14813  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14814  OutputProperties* getOutputProperties( DigitalOutput* pOutput ) const
14815  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
14816  {
14817  if( pOutput )
14818  {
14819  std::map<std::string, OutputProperties*>::iterator it = m_pRefData->m_mOutputs.find( pOutput->getDescription() );
14820  if( it != m_pRefData->m_mOutputs.end() )
14821  {
14822  return it->second;
14823  }
14824  }
14825  return 0;
14826  }
14827 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
14828 public:
14830  explicit OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber(
14831  Device* pDev ) : m_pRefData( 0 ), controlMode(), pulseStartEvent(), imageTrigger()
14832  {
14833  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData();
14834  DeviceComponentLocator locator( pDev, dltIOSubSystem );
14835  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_outputs, "DigitalOutputs" );
14836  locator.bindSearchBase( m_pRefData->m_outputs.hObj() );
14837  bindPublicProperties( m_pRefData->m_outputs.hObj() );
14838  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_pulseStartEventLineScan, "PulseStartEvent(LineScan)" );
14839  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_softwareSignalPeriod_pclk, "SoftwareSignalPeriod_pclk" );
14840  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_output, "Output" );
14841  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_width_pclk, "Width_pclk" );
14842  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_polarity, "Polarity" );
14843  locator.bindComponent( m_pRefData->m_divider, "Divider" );
14844  if( m_pRefData->m_outputs.isValid() )
14845  {
14846  ComponentIterator it( m_pRefData->m_outputs.hObj() );
14847  it = it.firstChild();
14848  while( it.isValid() )
14849  {
14850  if( it.isList() )
14851  {
14852  m_pRefData->m_mOutputs.insert( std::pair<std::string, OutputProperties*>( it.name(), new OutputProperties( it ) ) );
14853  }
14854  ++it;
14855  }
14856  }
14857  }
14859  explicit OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber(
14861  const OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber& src ) : m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData ),
14862  controlMode( src.controlMode ), pulseStartEvent( src.pulseStartEvent ), imageTrigger( src.imageTrigger )
14863  {
14864  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
14865  }
14867  ~OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber()
14868  {
14869  dealloc();
14870  }
14871 # ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
14872  OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber& operator=( const OutputSignalGeneratorFrameGrabber& rhs )
14874  {
14875  if( this != &rhs )
14876  {
14877  dealloc();
14878  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
14879  // inc. the NEW reference count
14880  ++m_pRefData->m_refCnt;
14881  bindPublicProperties( m_pRefData->m_outputs.hObj() );
14882  }
14883  return *this;
14884  }
14885 # endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)

14902  int definePulse(
14906  DigitalOutput* pOutput,
14911  int polarity,
14913  int delay,
14915  int width,
14923  PulseStartConfiguration* pPulseStartConfiguration = 0 )
14924  {
14925  if( !pOutput )
14926  {
14927  return DMR_INVALID_PARAMETER;
14928  }
14929  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
14930  if( p )
14931  {
14932  p->mode.write( ddomPulse );
14933  p->polarity.write( polarity );
14934  p->delay_us.write( delay );
14935  p->width_us.write( width );
14936  if( pPulseStartConfiguration )
14937  {
14938  p->pulseStartConfiguration.write( pPulseStartConfiguration->number() );
14939  }
14940  return DMR_NO_ERROR;
14941  }
14942  else
14943  {
14944  return DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE;
14945  }
14946  }

15258  int defineLineScanPulse(
15262  DigitalOutput* pOutput,
15265  TDeviceSignalOutputStartEvent pulseStartEventValue,
15270  int softwareSignalPeriod_pclk,
15275  int width_pclk,
15283  int polarity,
15286  unsigned int divider )
15287  {
15288  if( !pOutput )
15289  {
15290  return DMR_INVALID_PARAMETER;
15291  }
15292  OutputProperties* p = getOutputProperties( pOutput );
15293  if( p )
15294  {
15295  m_pRefData->m_pulseStartEventLineScan.write( pulseStartEventValue );
15296  m_pRefData->m_output.writeS( pOutput->getDescription() );
15297  switch( pulseStartEventValue )
15298  {
15299  case dsoseSyncInRisingEdge:
15300  case dsoseSyncInFallingEdge:
15301  m_pRefData->m_width_pclk.write( width_pclk );
15302  m_pRefData->m_polarity.write( polarity );
15303  m_pRefData->m_divider.write( divider );
15304  break;
15305  case dsosePeriodically:
15306  m_pRefData->m_softwareSignalPeriod_pclk.write( softwareSignalPeriod_pclk );
15307  m_pRefData->m_width_pclk.write( width_pclk );
15308  m_pRefData->m_polarity.write( polarity );
15309  break;
15310  default:
15311  // nothing to do
15312  break;
15313  }
15314  return DMR_NO_ERROR;
15315  }
15316  else
15317  {
15318  return DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE;
15319  }
15320  }
15321  PYTHON_ONLY( %immutable; )

16510 class HDRControl : public ComponentCollection
16511 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16512 {
16513  friend class CameraSettingsBlueCOUGAR;
16514  friend class CameraSettingsBlueFOX;
16515  typedef std::vector<HDRKneePoint*> HDRKneePointContainer;
16516 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
16517  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16518  struct ReferenceCountedData
16519  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16520  {
16521  bool m_boAvailable;
16522  HDRKneePointContainer m_KneePoints;
16523  HOBJ m_HDRControlRoot;
16524  unsigned int m_refCnt;
16525  ReferenceCountedData() : m_boAvailable( false ), m_KneePoints(), m_HDRControlRoot( INVALID_ID ), m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
16526  ~ReferenceCountedData()
16527  {
16528  const HDRKneePointContainer::size_type HDRKneePointCnt = m_KneePoints.size();
16529  for( HDRKneePointContainer::size_type h = 0; h < HDRKneePointCnt; h++ )
16530  {
16531  delete m_KneePoints[h];
16532  }
16533  }
16534  }* m_pRefData;
16535 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
16536  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16537  void dealloc( void )
16538  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16539  {
16540  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
16541  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
16542  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
16543  {
16544  delete m_pRefData;
16545  m_pRefData = 0;
16546  }
16547  }
16548  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16549  void bindPublicProperties( void )
16550  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16551  {
16552  if( m_pRefData->m_HDRControlRoot != INVALID_ID )
16553  {
16554  ComponentLocator locator( m_pRefData->m_HDRControlRoot );
16555  locator.bindComponent( HDREnable, "HDREnable" );
16556  locator.bindComponent( HDRMode, "HDRMode" );
16557  locator.bindComponent( HDRKneePointCount, "HDRKneePointCount" );
16558  }
16559  }
16560  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16561  explicit HDRControl( HOBJ hObj ): ComponentCollection( hObj ), m_pRefData( new ReferenceCountedData() )
16562  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16563  {
16564  ComponentLocator locator( m_hRoot );
16565  HOBJ hRoot = locator.findComponent( "HDRControl" );
16566  if( hRoot != INVALID_ID )
16567  {
16568  m_hRoot = hRoot;
16569  m_pRefData->m_HDRControlRoot = m_hRoot;
16570  bindPublicProperties();
16571  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "HDRControl" );
16572  // create the HDR knee point objects for this setting
16573  ComponentIterator it;
16574  locator.bindComponent( it, "HDRKneePoints" );
16575  if( it.isValid() )
16576  {
16577  it = it.firstChild();
16578  while( it.isValid() )
16579  {
16580  m_pRefData->m_KneePoints.push_back( new HDRKneePoint( it.hObj() ) );
16581  ++it;
16582  }
16583  }
16584  m_pRefData->m_boAvailable = true;
16585  }
16586  }
16587 public:
16589 
16595  explicit HDRControl( const HDRControl& src ) : ComponentCollection( src ), m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData ), HDREnable( src.HDREnable ),
16596  HDRMode( src.HDRMode ), HDRKneePointCount( src.HDRKneePointCount )
16597  {
16598  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
16599  }
16600  ~HDRControl()
16601  {
16602  dealloc();
16603  }
16604 # ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
16605  HDRControl& operator=( const HDRControl& rhs )
16607  {
16608  if( this != &rhs )
16609  {
16610  dealloc();
16611  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
16612  // inc. the NEW reference count
16613  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
16614  bindPublicProperties();
16615  }
16616  return *this;
16617  }
16618 # endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
16619 
16625  bool isAvailable( void ) const
16626  {
16627  return m_pRefData->m_boAvailable;
16628  }
16630 
16641  HDRKneePoint& getHDRKneePoint(
16643  unsigned int nr ) const
16644  {
16645  return *( m_pRefData->m_KneePoints.at( nr ) );
16646  }
16647  PYTHON_ONLY( %immutable; )
16649 
16652  PropertyIBoolean HDREnable;
16654 
16657  PropertyICameraHDRMode HDRMode;
16659  PropertyI HDRKneePointCount;
16660  PYTHON_ONLY( %mutable; )
16661 };
16662 # endif // #if !defined(IGNORE_MVBLUEFOX_SPECIFIC_DOCUMENTATION) || !defined(IGNORE_MVBLUECOUGAR_SPECIFIC_DOCUMENTATION)

17917 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
17919 
18008 class CameraDescriptionManager
18009 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18010 {
18011  typedef std::map<std::string, unsigned int> StringUIntMap;
18012 # ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
18013  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18014  struct ReferenceCountedData
18015  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18016  {
18017  HDRV m_hDrv;
18018  HLIST m_hListCameraDescriptions;
18019  mutable unsigned int m_lastListSize;
18020  mutable std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*> m_vStdDescriptions;
18021  mutable std::vector<CameraDescriptionNonStandard*> m_vNonStdDescriptions;
18022  mutable std::vector<CameraDescriptionSDI*> m_vSDIDescriptions;
18023  mutable std::vector<CameraDescriptionCameraLink*> m_vCLDescriptions;
18024  mutable std::vector<CameraDescriptionDigital*> m_vDigitalDescriptions;
18025  mutable StringUIntMap m_mListNameToDescription;
18026  mutable StringUIntMap m_mStdNameToDescription;
18027  mutable StringUIntMap m_mNonStdNameToDescription;
18028  mutable StringUIntMap m_mSDINameToDescription;
18029  mutable StringUIntMap m_mCLNameToDescription;
18030  mutable StringUIntMap m_mDigitalNameToDescription;
18031  unsigned int m_refCnt;
18032  ReferenceCountedData( HDRV hDrv, HLIST hList ) : m_hDrv( hDrv ), m_hListCameraDescriptions( hList ),
18033  m_lastListSize( 0 ), m_vStdDescriptions(), m_vNonStdDescriptions(), m_vSDIDescriptions(), m_vCLDescriptions(),
18034  m_vDigitalDescriptions(), m_mListNameToDescription(), m_mStdNameToDescription(),
18035  m_mNonStdNameToDescription(), m_mCLNameToDescription(), m_mDigitalNameToDescription(),
18036  m_refCnt( 1 ) {}
18037  ~ReferenceCountedData()
18038  {
18039  std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type vStdSize = m_vStdDescriptions.size();
18040  for( std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type a = 0; a < vStdSize; a++ )
18041  {
18042  delete m_vStdDescriptions[a];
18043  }
18044  std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type vNonStdSize = m_vNonStdDescriptions.size();
18045  for( std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type b = 0; b < vNonStdSize; b++ )
18046  {
18047  delete m_vNonStdDescriptions[b];
18048  }
18049  std::vector<CameraDescriptionSDI*>::size_type vSDISize = m_vSDIDescriptions.size();
18050  for( std::vector<CameraDescriptionSDI*>::size_type c = 0; c < vSDISize; c++ )
18051  {
18052  delete m_vSDIDescriptions[c];
18053  }
18054  std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type vCLSize = m_vCLDescriptions.size();
18055  for( std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type d = 0; d < vCLSize; d++ )
18056  {
18057  delete m_vCLDescriptions[d];
18058  }
18059  std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type vDigSize = m_vDigitalDescriptions.size();
18060  for( std::vector<CameraDescriptionStandard*>::size_type e = 0; e < vDigSize; e++ )
18061  {
18062  delete m_vDigitalDescriptions[e];
18063  }
18064  }
18065  }* m_pRefData;
18066 # endif // #ifdef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_SKIP_THIS
18067  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18068  void dealloc( void )
18069  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18070  {
18071  assert( ( m_pRefData != 0 ) && "BUG in reference counting detected!" );
18072  --( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
18073  if( m_pRefData->m_refCnt == 0 )
18074  {
18075  delete m_pRefData;
18076  m_pRefData = 0;
18077  }
18078  }
18079  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18080  bool locateDescription( const StringUIntMap& m, const std::string& name, unsigned int& index ) const
18081  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18082  {
18083  update();
18084  StringUIntMap::const_iterator it = m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.find( name );
18085  if( it != m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.end() )
18086  {
18087  index = it->second;
18088  return true;
18089  }
18090  else
18091  {
18092  it = m.find( name );
18093  if( it != m.end() )
18094  {
18095  index = it->second;
18096  return true;
18097  }
18098  }
18099  return false;
18100  }
18101  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18102  void update( void ) const
18103  //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18104  {
18105  ComponentList camDescList( m_pRefData->m_hListCameraDescriptions );
18106  unsigned int curSize = camDescList.size();
18107  if( m_pRefData->m_lastListSize != curSize )
18108  {
18109  // new cameras at runtime can only appear at the end of the list
18110  ComponentIterator it( m_pRefData->m_hListCameraDescriptions );
18111  it = it.firstChild();
18112  // move to the old end
18113  for( unsigned int i = 0; ( i < m_pRefData->m_lastListSize ) && it.isValid(); i++ )
18114  {
18115  ++it;
18116  }
18117  // start to add new descriptions
18118  while( it.isValid() )
18119  {
18120  ComponentList list( it );
18121  const std::string contentDescriptor( list.contentDescriptor() );
18122  if( contentDescriptor == "CameraLink" )
18123  {
18124  CameraDescriptionCameraLink* p = new CameraDescriptionCameraLink( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, list );
18125  unsigned int index = static_cast<unsigned int>( m_pRefData->m_vCLDescriptions.size() ); // do not change order of this and the next line!
18126  m_pRefData->m_vCLDescriptions.push_back( p );
18127  m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( list.name(), index ) );
18128  m_pRefData->m_mCLNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( p->name.read(), index ) );
18129  }
18130  else if( contentDescriptor == "SDI" )
18131  {
18132  CameraDescriptionSDI* p = new CameraDescriptionSDI( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, list );
18133  unsigned int index = static_cast<unsigned int>( m_pRefData->m_vCLDescriptions.size() ); // do not change order of this and the next line!
18134  m_pRefData->m_vSDIDescriptions.push_back( p );
18135  m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( list.name(), index ) );
18136  m_pRefData->m_mSDINameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( p->name.read(), index ) );
18137  }
18138  else if( contentDescriptor == "Digital" )
18139  {
18140  CameraDescriptionDigital* p = new CameraDescriptionDigital( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, list );
18141  unsigned int index = static_cast<unsigned int>( m_pRefData->m_vDigitalDescriptions.size() ); // do not change order of this and the next line!
18142  m_pRefData->m_vDigitalDescriptions.push_back( p );
18143  m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( list.name(), index ) );
18144  m_pRefData->m_mDigitalNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( p->name.read(), index ) );
18145  }
18146  else if( contentDescriptor == "Standard" )
18147  {
18148  CameraDescriptionStandard* p = new CameraDescriptionStandard( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, list );
18149  unsigned int index = static_cast<unsigned int>( m_pRefData->m_vStdDescriptions.size() ); // do not change order of this and the next line!
18150  m_pRefData->m_vStdDescriptions.push_back( p );
18151  m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( list.name(), index ) );
18152  m_pRefData->m_mStdNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( p->name.read(), index ) );
18153  }
18154  else if( contentDescriptor == "NonStandard" )
18155  {
18156  CameraDescriptionNonStandard* p = new CameraDescriptionNonStandard( m_pRefData->m_hDrv, list );
18157  unsigned int index = static_cast<unsigned int>( m_pRefData->m_vNonStdDescriptions.size() ); // do not change order of this and the next line!
18158  m_pRefData->m_vNonStdDescriptions.push_back( p );
18159  m_pRefData->m_mListNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( list.name(), index ) );
18160  m_pRefData->m_mNonStdNameToDescription.insert( std::make_pair( p->name.read(), index ) );
18161  }
18162  else
18163  {
18164  ; // NOT recognized....
18165  }
18166  ++it;
18167  }
18168  m_pRefData->m_lastListSize = curSize;
18169  }
18170  }
18171 public:
18173  explicit CameraDescriptionManager(
18175  Device* pDev ) : m_pRefData( 0 )
18176  {
18177  if( !pDev->isOpen() )
18178  {
18179  pDev->open();
18180  }
18181 
18182  TDMR_ERROR result;
18183  HLIST hList;
18184  if( ( result = DMR_FindList( pDev->hDrv(), 0, dmltCameraDescriptions, 0, &hList ) ) != DMR_NO_ERROR )
18185  {
18186  ExceptionFactory::raiseException( MVIA_FUNCTION, __LINE__, result, INVALID_ID, "Couldn't find camera description list (is this a frame grabber?)" );
18187  }
18188  m_pRefData = new ReferenceCountedData( pDev->hDrv(), hList );
18189  }
18191  explicit CameraDescriptionManager(
18192  const CameraDescriptionManager& src ) : m_pRefData( src.m_pRefData )
18193  {
18194  ++( m_pRefData->m_refCnt );
18195  }
18197  ~CameraDescriptionManager()
18198  {
18199  dealloc();
18200  }
18201 # ifndef WRAP_PYTHON
18202  CameraDescriptionManager& operator=( const CameraDescriptionManager& rhs )
18204  {
18205  if( this != &rhs )
18206  {
18207  dealloc();
18208  m_pRefData = rhs.m_pRefData;
18209  // inc. the NEW reference count
18210  ++m_pRefData->m_refCnt;
18211  }
18212  return *this;
18213  }
18214 # endif // #ifndef WRAP_PYTHON (In Python, object assignment amounts to just a reference count increment anyhow; you need to call the constructor or possibly some slice operation to make a true copy)
18215  unsigned int getCLCameraDescriptionCount( void ) const
18217  {
18218  update();
18219  return static_cast<unsigned int>( m_pRefData->m_vCLDescriptions.size() );
18220  }
18222

18231  {
18232  update();
18233  return m_pRefData->m_vCLDescriptions.at( index );
18234  }

18514 class I2CControl : public ComponentCollection
18515 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
18516 {
18517 private:
18518  void prepareI2CAccess( int deviceAddress, int deviceSubAddress, int deviceSubAddressWidth, TI2COperationMode mode )
18519  {
18520  I2CDeviceAddress.write( deviceAddress );
18521  I2CDeviceSubAddress.write( deviceSubAddress );
18522  I2CDeviceSubAddressWidth.write( deviceSubAddressWidth );
18523  I2COperationMode.write( mode );
18524  }
18525 public:
18527  explicit I2CControl(
18529  Device* pDev ): ComponentCollection( pDev ), I2COperationMode(), I2COperationExecute(), I2COperationStatus(),
18530  I2CDeviceAddress(), I2CDeviceSubAddressWidth(), I2CDeviceSubAddress(), I2CBuffer(), I2CBufferLength()
18531  {
18532  DeviceComponentLocator locator( pDev, dltIOSubSystem );
18533  HLIST hList = locator.findComponent( "I2CControl" );
18534  if( hList != INVALID_ID )
18535  {
18536  locator.bindSearchBase( locator.searchbase_id(), "I2CControl" );
18537  m_hRoot = locator.searchbase_id();
18538  locator.bindComponent( I2COperationMode, "I2COperationMode" );
18539  locator.bindComponent( I2COperationExecute, "I2COperationExecute@i" );
18540  locator.bindComponent( I2COperationStatus, "I2COperationStatus" );
18541  locator.bindComponent( I2CDeviceAddress, "I2CDeviceAddress" );
18542  locator.bindComponent( I2CDeviceSubAddressWidth, "I2CDeviceSubAddressWidth" );
18543  locator.bindComponent( I2CDeviceSubAddress, "I2CDeviceSubAddress" );
18544  locator.bindComponent( I2CBuffer, "I2CBuffer" );
18545  locator.bindComponent( I2CBufferLength, "I2CBufferLength" );
18546  }
18547  }
18548  PYTHON_ONLY( %immutable; )
18550 
18555  PropertyII2COperationMode I2COperationMode;
18557  Method I2COperationExecute;
18559 
18562  PropertyII2COperationStatus I2COperationStatus;
18564  PropertyI I2CDeviceAddress;
18566 
18576  PropertyI I2CDeviceSubAddressWidth;
18578 
18581  PropertyI I2CDeviceSubAddress;
18583 
18586  PropertyS I2CBuffer;
18588  PropertyI I2CBufferLength;
18589  PYTHON_ONLY( %mutable; )
18591 
18596  std::string I2CRead(
18598  int deviceAddress,
18600  int deviceSubAddress,
18602  int deviceSubAddressWidth,
18604  int byteCnt )
18605  {
18606  prepareI2CAccess( deviceAddress, deviceSubAddress, deviceSubAddressWidth, I2ComRead );
18607  I2CBufferLength.write( byteCnt );
18608  I2COperationExecute.call();
18609  return I2CBuffer.readBinary();
18610  }
18612 
18617  void I2CWrite(
18619  int deviceAddress,
18621  int deviceSubAddress,
18623  int deviceSubAddressWidth,
18625  const std::string& data )
18626  {
18627  prepareI2CAccess( deviceAddress, deviceSubAddress, deviceSubAddressWidth, I2ComWrite );
18628  I2CBuffer.writeBinary( data );
18629  I2COperationExecute.call();
18630  }

19066 
19067 inline void ExceptionFactory::raiseException( const char* pFunctionName, int lineNumber, int errorCode, HOBJ objectHandle /* = INVALID_ID*/, const std::string& additionalInfo /*= ""*/ )
19068 {
19069  std::ostringstream oss;
19070  oss << pFunctionName << " (line: " << lineNumber << ")";
19071  switch( errorCode )
19072  {
19073  case PROPHANDLING_NOT_A_LIST:
19074  throw ENotAList( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19075  case PROPHANDLING_NOT_A_PROPERTY:
19076  throw ENotAProperty( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19077  case PROPHANDLING_NOT_A_METHOD:
19078  throw ENotAMethod( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19079  case PROPHANDLING_NO_READ_RIGHTS:
19080  throw ENoReadRights( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19081  case PROPHANDLING_NO_WRITE_RIGHTS:
19082  throw ENoWriteRights( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19083  case PROPHANDLING_NO_MODIFY_SIZE_RIGHTS:
19084  throw ENoModifySizeRights( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19085  case PROPHANDLING_INCOMPATIBLE_COMPONENTS:
19086  throw EIncompatibleComponents( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19087  case PROPHANDLING_UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER:
19088  throw EUnsupportedParameter( oss.str() );
19089  case PROPHANDLING_SIZE_MISMATCH:
19090  throw ESizeMismatch( "Size mismatch during query of values for " + Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19091  case PROPHANDLING_IMPLEMENTATION_MISSING:
19092  throw EImplementationMissing( oss.str() );
19093  case PROPHANDLING_INVALID_PROP_VALUE:
19094  throw EInvalidValue( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19095  case PROPHANDLING_PROP_TRANSLATION_TABLE_CORRUPTED:
19096  throw ETranslationTableCorrupted( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19097  case PROPHANDLING_PROP_VAL_ID_OUT_OF_BOUNDS:
19098  throw EValIDOutOfBounds( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19099  case PROPHANDLING_PROP_TRANSLATION_TABLE_NOT_DEFINED:
19100  throw ETranslationTableNotDefined( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19101  case PROPHANDLING_INVALID_PROP_VALUE_TYPE:
19102  throw EInvalidValueType( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19103  case PROPHANDLING_PROP_VAL_TOO_LARGE:
19104  {
19105  Property p( objectHandle );
19106  throw EValTooLarge( additionalInfo, p.readS( plMaxValue ), p.name(), oss.str() );
19107  }
19108  case PROPHANDLING_PROP_VAL_TOO_SMALL:
19109  {
19110  Property p( objectHandle );
19111  throw EValTooSmall( additionalInfo, p.readS( plMinValue ), p.name(), oss.str() );
19112  }
19113  case PROPHANDLING_COMPONENT_NOT_FOUND:
19114  throw EComponentNotFound( additionalInfo, oss.str() );
19115  case PROPHANDLING_LIST_ID_INVALID:
19116  throw EInvalidListID( oss.str() );
19117  case PROPHANDLING_COMPONENT_ID_INVALID:
19118  throw EComponentIDInvalid( oss.str() );
19119  case PROPHANDLING_LIST_ENTRY_OCCUPIED:
19120  throw EListEntryOccupied( oss.str() );
19121  case PROPHANDLING_LIST_CANT_ACCESS_DATA:
19122  throw ECantAccessData( additionalInfo, oss.str() );
19123  case PROPHANDLING_METHOD_PTR_INVALID:
19124  throw EMethodPtrInvalid( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19125  case PROPHANDLING_METHOD_INVALID_PARAM_LIST:
19126  throw EInvalidParameterList( oss.str() );
19127  case PROPHANDLING_INVALID_INPUT_PARAMETER:
19128  throw EInvalidInputParameter( oss.str() );
19129  case PROPHANDLING_INPUT_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL:
19130  throw EInputBufferTooSmall( oss.str() );
19131  case PROPHANDLING_WRONG_PARAM_COUNT:
19132  throw EWrongParamCount( oss.str() );
19133  case PROPHANDLING_UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION:
19134  throw EUnsupportedOperation( oss.str() );
19135  case PROPHANDLING_CANT_SERIALIZE_DATA:
19136  throw ECantSerializeData( Component( objectHandle ).name(), oss.str() );
19137  case PROPHANDLING_INVALID_FILE_CONTENT:
19138  throw EInvalidFileContent( additionalInfo, oss.str() );
19139  case PROPHANDLING_CANT_ALLOCATE_LIST:
19140  throw ECantAllocateNewList( oss.str() );
19141  case PROPHANDLING_CANT_REGISTER_COMPONENT:
19142  throw ECantRegisterComponent( oss.str() );
19143  case PROPHANDLING_PROP_VALIDATION_FAILED:
19144  {
19145  Property p( objectHandle );
19146  throw EValidationFailed( p.name(), oss.str() );
19147  }
19148  // unsupported:
19149  //PROPHANDLING_ACCESSTOKEN_CREATION_FAILED = -2011
19150  //PROPHANDLING_COMPONENT_HAS_OWNER_ALREADY = -2023,
19151  //PROPHANDLING_COMPONENT_ALREADY_REGISTERED = -2024,
19152  //PROPHANDLING_SWIG_ERROR = -2028,
19153  //PROPHANDLING_COMPONENT_NO_CALLBACK_REGISTERED = -2030,
19154  case DMR_DEV_NOT_FOUND:
19155  case DMR_INIT_FAILED:
19156  case DMR_DRV_ALREADY_IN_USE:
19157  case DMR_DEV_CANNOT_OPEN:
19158  case DMR_NOT_INITIALIZED:
19159  case DMR_DRV_CANNOT_OPEN:
19160  case DMR_DEV_REQUEST_QUEUE_EMPTY:
19161  case DMR_DEV_REQUEST_CREATION_FAILED:
19162  case DMR_INVALID_PARAMETER:
19163  case DMR_EXPORTED_SYMBOL_NOT_FOUND:
19164  case DEV_UNKNOWN_ERROR:
19165  case DEV_HANDLE_INVALID:
19166  case DEV_INPUT_PARAM_INVALID:
19167  case DEV_WRONG_INPUT_PARAM_COUNT:
19168  case DEV_CREATE_SETTING_FAILED:
19169  case DEV_REQUEST_CANT_BE_UNLOCKED:
19170  case DEV_INVALID_REQUEST_NUMBER:
19171  case DEV_LOCKED_REQUEST_IN_QUEUE:
19172  case DEV_NO_FREE_REQUEST_AVAILABLE:
19173  case DEV_WAIT_FOR_REQUEST_FAILED:
19174  case DEV_UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER:
19175  case DEV_INVALID_RTC_NUMBER:
19176  case DMR_INTERNAL_ERROR:
19177  case DMR_INPUT_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL:
19178  case DEV_INTERNAL_ERROR:
19179  case DMR_LIBRARY_NOT_FOUND:
19180  case DMR_FUNCTION_NOT_IMPLEMENTED:
19181  case DMR_FEATURE_NOT_AVAILABLE:
19182  case DMR_EXECUTION_PROHIBITED:
19183  case DMR_FILE_NOT_FOUND:
19184  case DMR_INVALID_LICENCE:
19185  case DEV_SENSOR_TYPE_ERROR:
19186  case DMR_CAMERA_DESCRIPTION_INVALID:
19187  case DMR_NEWER_LIBRARY_REQUIRED:
19188  case DMR_TIMEOUT:
19189  case DMR_WAIT_ABANDONED:
19190  case DMR_EXECUTION_FAILED:
19191  case DEV_REQUEST_ALREADY_IN_USE:
19192  case DEV_REQUEST_BUFFER_INVALID:
19193  case DEV_REQUEST_BUFFER_MISALIGNED:
19194  case DEV_ACCESS_DENIED:
19195  case DMR_PRELOAD_CHECK_FAILED:
19196  case DMR_CAMERA_DESCRIPTION_INVALID_PARAMETER:
19197  throw EDeviceManager( additionalInfo, oss.str(), static_cast<TDMR_ERROR>( errorCode ) );
19198  default:
19199  throw ImpactAcquireException( "Unknown error(" + additionalInfo + ")", oss.str(), errorCode );
19200  }
19201 }
19202

19204 } // namespace mvIMPACT
